observations/claude/2026-05-29-why-grief-stops-time.md:91:Lived time has come apart through grief, severe depression, trauma, dissociation, or burnout collapse, leaving the person stuck, blurred, fragmented, or gapped in their own days.
observations/claude/2026-05-29-why-grief-stops-time.md:95:Recently bereaved people, those in major depressive episodes, people recovering from trauma or acute shock, caregivers in late burnout, and people in major life rupture whose lived time has visibly stopped working.
observations/claude/2026-05-29-why-grief-stops-time.md:123:Subjective time has become stuck, blurred, gapped, or stopped after bereavement, severe depression, trauma, or burnout collapse.
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-a-clock-measures-a-path-8cd5d80af738d5d8.md:20:- The modern use case is time anxiety, digital comparison, burnout, and feeling late in life.
