reviews/originality/2026-05-30-stratified-post-negation-authorization-940b94daf10fd12f.json:127:  "novelty_adjustment": "Lower novelty from 0.74 to 0.42. The idea is not a discovery of a new structure by itself. Its components are close to contextualism, doctrine-as-grammar, discursive-tradition analysis, Madhyamaka non-positioning, Advaita self-luminosity debates, contemplative-experience support literature, and prior Lumenary inference-policy records. The useful contribution is a tighter protocol: post-negation authorization should be coded by source stratum, level of claim, and practitioner effect, with analyst-frame refusal and explicit failure rules. Human-condition fit is plausible but narrow: stable practitioners or readers with identity distress, meaning loss, spiritual inflation, nihilistic deflation, or neuroscience-mediated overinterpretation after quiet states. It is not suitable for active OCD or scrupulosity, dissociation, psychosis, mania, severe depression, trauma activation, addiction withdrawal, medical blackout concerns, or situations needing clinical care rather than interpretive refinement.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-stop-when-time-is-up-not-when-it-feels-done-4b185ee8c360296e.md:12:Some reflective work has no natural internal end, especially for people prone to compulsive self-examination, perfectionism, or achievement-contingent self-worth. For those cases, completion should be defined before starting by an external limit, such as a fixed time or one bounded action, and the question should close for the day even if it does not feel resolved. A method has surrendered its hold when the practitioner can stop on schedule, not when reflection finally feels complete.
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-stop-when-time-is-up-not-when-it-feels-done-4b185ee8c360296e.md:19:- Continuing past the chosen limit is often avoidance, reassurance seeking, or perfectionism disguised as diligence.
