reviews/originality/2026-05-30-some-silence-needs-a-second-voice-2c70888346a6050d.md:48:- Ignatius of Loyola, Spiritual Exercises, Rules and Annotations, https://spiritualexercises.neocities.org/: overlap: Very close on delayed trust in interior states, examining post-consolation resolutions before acting, and disclosing hidden temptations to a confessor or competent spiritual person.; difference: Ignatius is theological, staged, and director-mediated, not a secular post-quiet protocol for loneliness and achievement-contingent self-worth.; novelty impact: Strong reduction. The second-voice architecture is old, though the modern cohort framing is narrower.
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-some-silence-needs-a-second-voice-2c70888346a6050d.md:49:- Lindahl et al., Varieties of Contemplative Experience, PLOS ONE 2017, https://journals.plos.org/plosone/article?id=10.1371/journal.pone.0176239: overlap: Close on meditation-related challenges, interpretation, social context, teacher or clinician response, remedies, and the role of others in meaning-making.; difference: VCE is descriptive and broad. The candidate prescribes a simple relational delay after quiet states.; novelty impact: Moderate reduction. This is a practice-facing distillation of known support-routing concerns.
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-some-silence-needs-a-second-voice-2c70888346a6050d.md:53:- U.S. Surgeon General Advisory on loneliness and social connection, https://www.hhs.gov/sites/default/files/surgeon-general-social-connection-advisory.pdf: overlap: Supports the modern wound: isolation can make people carry identity and meaning burdens without durable belonging.; difference: This grounds cohort fit, not originality of the contemplative structure.; novelty impact: Improves human-condition relevance but does not raise novelty.
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-some-silence-needs-a-second-voice-2c70888346a6050d.md:70:- If: The helper must be bounded and anti-reassurance. Then: A helper protocol that validates distress, refuses repeated certainty-seeking, and returns the person to ordinary care outperforms unstructured reassurance. Weakens if: Repeated reassurance performs as well, or bounded support increases anxiety, shame, or relational control. Test surface: Pilot stratified by reassurance seeking, intolerance of uncertainty, loneliness, and contingencies of self-worth.
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-some-silence-needs-a-second-voice-2c70888346a6050d.md:72:- If: Human-condition benefit is cohort-specific. Then: Benefits are strongest for stable isolated, perfectionistic, or achievement-contingent practitioners and absent or harmful for active OCD, scrupulosity, dissociation, mania, severe depression, trauma activation, addiction withdrawal, unsafe authority, or medical blackout concerns. Weakens if: Effects are not moderated by loneliness, self-worth contingency, or checking risk, or adverse effects cluster in the intended cohort. Test surface: Screened two-week pilot with loneliness, rumination, self-worth contingency, reassurance seeking, adverse meditation-effect, and ordinary-action measures.
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-some-silence-needs-a-second-voice-2c70888346a6050d.md:102:Structural translation: When a person is prone to self-worth verdicts, asking them to classify the meaning of an ambiguous event can amplify the wound. A bounded second-person or rule-held review plus one concrete duty should reduce rumination.
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-some-silence-needs-a-second-voice-2c70888346a6050d.md:104:Prediction: High-perfectionism students, engineers, clinicians, or researchers who receive one bounded review plus one repair action will show less shame, less defensive interpretation, and faster useful action than those assigned solo meta-analysis of what the event says about them.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-layered-authorization-of-beginning-8a8d544ce3b6f17a.md:53:- Berger's plausibility-structure theory, summarized in The SAGE Encyclopedia of the Sociology of Religion, https://sk.sagepub.com/ency/edvol/embed/the-sage-encyclopedia-of-sociology-of-religion/chpt/plausibility-structure: overlap: Close for religious meaning being sustained by social contexts, institutions, recognition, naming, and internalization.; difference: The candidate adds micro-level agency authorization and transfer thresholds.; novelty impact: Moderate reduction. Institutional selection and social affordance are already well anticipated.
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-restating-is-not-realizing-1ed7e902d1f20ee6.md:73:- If: The Duplicate Check helps high-output overproducers but not under-producers. Then: Screened high-output participants show fewer redundant drafts and more concrete actions after four uses, without higher shame, rumination, or reduced genuinely new work. Weakens if: The prompt increases avoidance, shame, or underproduction, or ordinary WIP limits and planning prompts perform equally well. Test surface: Two-week pilot with WIP count, duplicate-output coding, action completion, rumination, shame, burnout, and novelty measures.
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-restating-is-not-realizing-1ed7e902d1f20ee6.md:116:Novelty adjustment: Lower novelty from 0.55 to 0.29. The live insight is a useful recursive application of an already logged Lumenary stopping rule. It should be merged with More Is Not The Same As Progress and The Answer You Keep Finding Is Already Settled. Human-condition fit is real but narrow: high-output researchers, writers, founders, students, and makers whose self-worth depends on continued production. It is not a fit for depressed under-producers, people in acute burnout who need rest, people under coercive workload, early exploratory phases without a real next action, or traditions where repetition is the practice itself.
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-restating-is-not-realizing-1ed7e902d1f20ee6.md:124:- Pilot The Duplicate Check only with high-output overproducers and screen out severe depression, acute burnout, coercive workload, under-production, shame spirals, and cases where ordinary editorial revision is the real task.
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-stop-when-time-is-up-not-when-it-feels-done-4b185ee8c360296e.json:13:    "Continuing past the chosen limit is often avoidance, reassurance seeking, or perfectionism disguised as diligence.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-stop-when-time-is-up-not-when-it-feels-done-4b185ee8c360296e.json:24:  "exact_claim": "Some reflective work has no natural internal end, especially for people prone to compulsive self-examination, perfectionism, or achievement-contingent self-worth. For those cases, completion should be defined before starting by an external limit, such as a fixed time or one bounded action, and the question should close for the day even if it does not feel resolved. A method has surrendered its hold when the practitioner can stop on schedule, not when reflection finally feels complete.",
