reviews/originality/2026-05-30-when-tools-become-judges-95d52440abfccb6a.md:47:- Internal Lumenary audit, The Method's Reckoning: What a Practice Does With Its Own Authority at Completion, reviews/originality/audits.jsonl, 2026-05-26: overlap: Already states that contemplative methods face a self-authority question at completion and proposes method-type as a predictor of verification and transmission.; difference: The current idea recasts the older typology as boundary operation plus custody, and gives it a burnout-facing practice warning.; novelty impact: Major reduction. This is mostly a revision of prior Lumenary work, not a new finding.
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-when-tools-become-judges-95d52440abfccb6a.md:49:- Joshua William Smith, Snakes and Ladders: Therapy as Liberation in Nagarjuna and Wittgenstein's Tractatus, Sophia 2021, https://link.springer.com/article/10.1007/s11841-020-00804-6: overlap: Very close for therapeutic methods that dissolve philosophical attachment and for the ladder or snake pattern of using a method that undercuts possessive thesis-making.; difference: Smith is a bilateral comparative philosophy argument, not a cross-tradition custody codebook or burnout practice protocol.; novelty impact: Strong reduction for the self-undermining method unit.
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-when-tools-become-judges-95d52440abfccb6a.md:52:- Cheetah House FAQ on meditation-related difficulties, https://www.cheetahhouse.org/faq: overlap: Supports the safety concern that practice can worsen anxiety, intrusive thoughts, dissociation, motivation, meaning, agency, and identity.; difference: It does not provide the two-axis authority model.; novelty impact: Improves safety grounding but does not increase originality.
