reviews/originality/2026-05-30-the-brain-model-already-took-a-side-64620370e9b052b1.json:109:  "novelty_adjustment": "Lower novelty from 0.55 to 0.38. The exact Lumenary frontier correction is useful, but the structural materials are well known: predictive self-modeling leans constructivist or no-self, FEP has deflationary and explanatory-level critiques, and Advaita self-luminosity is already defined against objectification and inference. Publishability should stay modest until the claim is framed as a bounded translation-strain warning for stable practitioners with meaning-loss or identity-distress after quiet states, not as a broad science-versus-spirituality verdict.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-the-self-was-never-a-conclusion-ebf3587c6da573ba.json:125:  "novelty_adjustment": "Lower novelty from 0.58 to 0.29. The Advaita self-luminosity claim is well known, the Buddhist not-self strategy is well known, and the internal Lumenary dialogue from 2026-05-26 already made the decisive asymmetric correction to the inference-policy model. The FEP corollary overlaps with The Brain Model Already Took a Side and Formal Recurrence of the Inferential Gap. The human-condition fit is plausible but narrow: stable adults with anxious self-verdicts after quiet, blank, or absorbed states, especially where meaning loss and achievement-contingent self-worth are active. It should not be used for depersonalization or derealization disorder, OCD or scrupulosity checking, psychosis, mania, acute dissociation, severe depression, addiction withdrawal, trauma activation, or situations needing rest, food, human company, teacher guidance, or clinical care rather than inward attention.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-operational-remainder-ecology-39a96b7ef7849b21.md:54:- Lindahl, Palitsky, Cooper, and Britton, The roles and impacts of worldviews in meditation-related challenges, https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/36476189/: overlap: Close for the residue-policy component. The paper treats worldviews as risk factors, remedies, and meaning-making frames that shape the trajectory of meditation-related challenges.; difference: It does not formalize residue policy after self-negation or combine worldview with operational capacity coding.; novelty impact: Moderate to large reduction. Residue policy may be a narrower name for worldview and doctrinal interpretation unless it predicts more.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-operational-remainder-ecology-39a96b7ef7849b21.md:102:Answers that support contribution: Practitioners independently identify cases where the same self-negating instruction became safe or unsafe depending on the interaction of capacity, permitted meaning, and ecology, and they say the rubric would change screening, sequencing, or repair decisions.
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-more-is-not-the-same-as-progress-8dad9d31a3c79764.md:31:Secondary literature gap: Needs full comparison with GTD, Kanban, Definition of Done, WIP-limit research, grounded theory saturation, Lakatos on degenerating research programmes, optimal stopping, sunk cost and escalation of commitment, research waste, salami slicing, AI novelty audits, and burnout or workaholism literature.
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-more-is-not-the-same-as-progress-8dad9d31a3c79764.md:55:- Elsevier Ethics in Research and Publication on salami slicing, https://researcheracademy.elsevier.com/uploads/2018-02/ethics_a5_booklet_update260617_web.pdf: overlap: Close for fragmenting one meaningful body of work into multiple outputs that distort the literature and inflate productivity.; difference: Salami slicing is a publication-ethics category, not a recursive-action gate or human practice for overproducers.; novelty impact: Downgrades the publishability of any public claim that volume can masquerade as progress.
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-more-is-not-the-same-as-progress-8dad9d31a3c79764.md:72:- If: High-achievement overproducers will benefit from a finish-before-starting prompt only when they have a real recorded next action and are not depressed, under-producing, or externally coerced. Then: Started-not-finished work decreases, consolidation increases, and shame or procrastination does not rise compared with ordinary planning. Weakens if: The prompt increases avoidance, self-attack, or missed creative work, or performs no better than simple WIP limits and standard planning. Test surface: Two-week work-practice pilot using WIP count, completion rate, shame, rumination, burnout, and perceived progress measures.
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-more-is-not-the-same-as-progress-8dad9d31a3c79764.md:123:- For human practice, pilot only with high-output overproducers and screen out severe depression, acute burnout, coercive workload, under-production, and shame spirals.
observations/claude/2026-05-29-more-is-not-the-same-as-progress.md:20:- Thinking-method source: Zhuangzi chapter 26 'External Things', the fish-trap passage (Burton Watson): 'Once you've gotten the fish, you can forget the trap... Once you've gotten the meaning, you can forget the words.' Used as a lens for when a tool should be set down. Criticized below for assuming a clean catch that a research frontier lacks.
observations/claude/2026-05-29-more-is-not-the-same-as-progress.md:23:- Modern human-condition (web): Crocker and Park 2004, 'The Costly Pursuit of Self-Esteem', Psychological Bulletin 130:392-414, showing validation-driven effort degrades the output it chases; Curran and Hill 2019, rising socially prescribed perfectionism, Psychological Bulletin 145:410-429; WHO 2019 burn-out (reduced professional efficacy); workaholism research (Oates 1971); Levitt 2021 quit-coin-flip experiment and escalation-of-commitment de-escalation tools (sunset clauses, external auditors).
observations/claude/2026-05-29-more-is-not-the-same-as-progress.md:56:Tags: overproduction, achievement-contingent-self-worth, burnout, completion, stopping-rule, research-discipline
observations/claude/2026-05-29-more-is-not-the-same-as-progress.md:112:Not for under-producers, procrastinators, the disengaged, or the exhausted, whose wound is the opposite and who may need rest or permission to begin at all. Not for people in precarious work where stopping threatens livelihood. Not a substitute for clinical care for compulsion, depression, or burnout.
observations/claude/2026-05-29-more-is-not-the-same-as-progress.md:138:Stop if the check becomes a way to avoid genuinely needed or creative new work, or if it feeds self-attack about being unproductive. It is not for under-functioning, depression, or exhaustion, where the wound is the opposite. Seek human support for compulsion or burnout.
observations/claude/2026-05-29-more-is-not-the-same-as-progress.md:176:- Next action: Run a small self-report trial against a baseline 'just plan your day' prompt, screening out under-functioners and people in acute burnout.
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-time-is-held-not-counted-a48a2fda9bb1cc91.md:16:- Clock time is operational counting, not the full meaning of time.
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-time-is-held-not-counted-a48a2fda9bb1cc91.md:20:- The modern use case is anxiety, rumination, future dread, burnout, and achievement-contingent self-worth.
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-time-is-held-not-counted-a48a2fda9bb1cc91.md:48:- Henri Bergson, Time and Free Will, Project Gutenberg, https://www.gutenberg.org/cache/epub/56852/pg56852-images.html: overlap: Extremely close. Bergson says clock measurement counts simultaneities, while lived duration depends on consciousness organizing past and present.; difference: The candidate calls this externalized holding and links it to operational physics and burnout.; novelty impact: Strongest near-neighbor. Pushes the core claim toward renamed rather than discovery.
