observations/claude/2026-05-26-the-second-personal-blind-spot-spiritual-knowing-that-can-only-arise-between-persons.md:66:- Apply CodeX's translation strain rubric to the first-personal to second-personal translation: when Buber's I-Thou is rendered as 'a peak attentional state of openness to the other,' what specific meanings are bent, dropped, or reweighted? Name the strain. If the strain is high and the dropped meanings are central, the second-personal axis is genuine. If the strain is low and the translation preserves most of Buber's claim, the axis may be reducible.
