reviews/originality/2026-05-29-the-road-must-know-its-end-ddc62528ba3f429d.md:48:- MN 22 Alagaddupama Sutta, https://www.dhammatalks.org/suttas/MN/MN22.html: overlap: Very close for right use followed by non-possession of the method after crossing.; difference: MN 22 is not a cross-tradition codebook and does not target modern burnout or achievement-contingent self-worth.; novelty impact: Major downgrade. The after-use release structure is known primary material.
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-the-road-must-know-its-end-ddc62528ba3f429d.md:51:- Michael Sells, Mystical Languages of Unsaying, https://press.uchicago.edu/ucp/books/book/chicago/M/bo3635525.html: overlap: Close for discourse and method that turn back on their own claims and prevent possession of the result.; difference: Sells is focused on apophatic discourse, not a cross-tradition after-use grid or burnout-oriented practice check.; novelty impact: Strong prior-art pressure against calling self-undermining method original.
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-the-road-must-know-its-end-ddc62528ba3f429d.md:69:- If: The After-Use Check helps the intended modern cohort. Then: Achievement-driven participants with high self-worth contingency report less rumination, comparison, and method-identity after using the check, without reduced responsibility. Weakens if: The check increases self-monitoring, shame, avoidance, or tool-performance pressure, or performs no better than generic journaling or rest-and-plan prompts. Test surface: Two-week randomized pilot stratified by perfectionism, burnout, self-worth contingency, and clinical-risk screen.
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-the-road-must-know-its-end-ddc62528ba3f429d.md:80:- Clinicians or coaches working with burnout and perfectionism
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-the-road-must-know-its-end-ddc62528ba3f429d.md:108:Novelty adjustment: Lower novelty from 0.61 to 0.31. The two-axis structure is already an internal audit instruction, and the individual components are strongly represented in MN 22, upaya, apophasis, Dogen, and therapeutic-method literature. Human-condition fit is real but narrow: achievement-driven people who convert methods and insights into worth. Non-fit cases include acute crisis, severe depression, addiction withdrawal, dissociation, psychosis, under-motivation, responsibility avoidance, and structural burnout where the primary remedy is workload or institutional change rather than reflection.
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-the-road-must-know-its-end-ddc62528ba3f429d.md:116:- Pilot The After-Use Check only with screening for perfectionism, scrupulosity, avoidance, workload coercion, dissociation, mania, trauma activation, severe depression, and clinical distress.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-whose-doing-is-this-credit-distribution-as-a-practice-variable-5e22b929e230f390.md:12:Credit distribution is a separable practice variable. Traditions distribute the power behind transformation across practitioner-centered, source-centered, split-credit, activity-centered, and ground-centered patterns, and those patterns shape the felt quality of effort, failure meanings, safeguards, and practice dangers.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-whose-doing-is-this-credit-distribution-as-a-practice-variable-5e22b929e230f390.md:72:- If: Dual-trained practitioners should experience different agency orientations when switching practices. Then: A practitioner trained in Theravada right effort and Jodo Shinshu entrusting, or Advaita inquiry and Soto just-sitting, can describe different felt meanings of effort, failure, and credit without being prompted with the typology. Weakens if: Practitioners report no felt agency shift, or the shift is fully explained by vocabulary, teacher style, devotional temperament, or institutional identity. Test surface: Micro-phenomenological interviews with dual-trained practitioners and teachers.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-whose-doing-is-this-credit-distribution-as-a-practice-variable-5e22b929e230f390.md:103:Prediction: Programs with similar tasks but different credit stories should show different failure patterns: burnout from self-credit, passivity from source-credit, performative compliance from activity-credit, and premature completion claims from ground-credit.
