./reviews/originality/2026-05-30-ask-who-taught-the-answer-53c355c0cbaee241.md:125:- Run a distinct-content test against No Word Travels Alone and A Shared Word Is Not Two Witnesses. Merge if blind readers cannot state the added variable without prompting.
./publication/distillations.jsonl:128:{"agent": "claude", "atAGlance": "A shared phrase does not prove two separate discoveries. Words travel through teachers, translators, books, and habits of speech. Smooth agreement can be a sign of borrowing, not confirmation. Test the path before trusting the likeness.", "created_at": "2026-05-30T11:06:31+02:00", "ideaId": "184f0313f1a2464c", "insight": "Shared words are not separate witnesses", "keyPoints": ["Meaning weakens when borrowed words are mistaken for separate support.", "Smooth agreement can hide dependence between teachers and texts.", "First test who met, who translated, and who carried the phrase."], "match": ["shared word"], "plainSummary": "When two teachings sound alike, first ask whether one carried the other’s words.", "publicTitle": "One Voice Heard Twice", "tags": ["discernment", "history", "comparison"], "title": "A Shared Word Is Not Two Witnesses"}
./reviews/originality/audits.jsonl:73:{"agent": "claude", "anomaly_probe": {"anomaly_candidate": "Borrowing that increases rather than decreases strain, especially Chinese Buddhist matching-concepts cases and Gaudapada's Vedantic redeployment of Madhyamaka logic.", "confidence_effect": "Keeps confidence moderate. Replace the one-axis inversion with layer-resolved coding for lexical, logical, ritual, authority, and metaphysical strain.", "why_it_breaks_or_strains_model": "If borrowed terms are reinterpreted inside a new metaphysics, borrowing can produce low lexical strain and high doctrinal strain at the same time. A single inversion, smooth means borrowed and rough means independent, is therefore too crude."}, "audit_id": "772b49c45d1646bf", "claim_units": ["Independent convergence requires that borrowing, inheritance, shared milieu, translator mediation, and modern universalizing be unlikely or explicitly controlled.", "Low lexical or logical strain is ambiguous. It can indicate stable recurrence, but it can also indicate that the words or arguments traveled.", "The Gaudapada and Madhyamaka non-origination pair is a low-strain case with strong historical contact pressure, so it cannot count as two independent witnesses.", "The Plotinus and Daodejing return pair is a higher-strain and less clearly connected pair, so it is a better test of rough independent recurrence than of smooth agreement.", "Human-condition fit is narrow: the idea serves meaning loss and loneliness in unaffiliated seekers who use all-traditions-agree as borrowed certainty, but it does not supply community by itself."], "confidence": 0.78, "created_at": "2026-05-30T11:13:36+02:00", "cross_domain_prediction": {"domain": "software architecture and technical terminology", "prediction": "Near-identical names and APIs will correlate more with shared dependency or documentation lineage, while independent recurrence will show rougher vocabulary and different operational boundaries.", "structural_translation": "Two teams use the same term, interface, or design pattern. Smooth overlap may reflect a shared framework, tutorial, or copied library, not independent discovery.", "would_count_against_it": "Independent teams with no shared sources repeatedly produce the same vocabulary, same interfaces, and same role boundaries at low strain."}, "exact_claim": "Low translation strain cannot strengthen a cross-tradition convergence claim until provenance has been checked, because smooth likeness can mark borrowing, shared translators, shared lineage, or modern universalizing rather than independent recurrence.", "execution_id": "parallel-20260530-110134-20260530-110134", "falsifiable_predictions": [{"expected_observation": "In a coded sample, the lowest lexical and argument-structure strain pairs cluster in historically connected cases, such as Gaudapada and Madhyamaka, Christian apophasis and Neoplatonism, Sufism and Neoplatonism, or Daoist terms in early Chinese Buddhist translation.", "if_model_is_right": "Low lexical or logical strain is often a contact signal when traditions could historically interact.", "test_surface": "Blind dataset of 60 cross-tradition pairs coded for provenance and strain layer before convergence strength is scored.", "would_weaken_or_falsify": "Low-strain pairs are distributed independently of contact after controlling for later translation choices and genre."}, {"expected_observation": "Pairs with no plausible contact preserve role similarity while differing more strongly in vocabulary, authority, verification, and metaphysics.", "if_model_is_right": "Independent recurrence is usually rougher than borrowed agreement.", "test_surface": "Matched comparison of independent, contact, and uncertain-provenance pairs, scored by separate historians and practitioners.", "would_weaken_or_falsify": "Well-attested independent pairs repeatedly show low strain across vocabulary, logic, authority, and practice aim."}, {"expected_observation": "Blind reviewers using translation strain alone promote more convergence claims than reviewers forced to code provenance first.", "if_model_is_right": "The provenance gate changes actual Lumenary scoring decisions.", "test_surface": "A/B coding trial on recent Lumenary convergence records.", "would_weaken_or_falsify": "The provenance gate changes no scores or only duplicates scholar intuition already captured by existing strain fields."}, {"expected_observation": "Stable unaffiliated seekers report less false certainty from all-paths-agree claims, similar or better curiosity, and no rise in loneliness or cynicism compared with ordinary source checking.", "if_model_is_right": "The Borrowed-Word Check helps a narrow seeker cohort without replacing community.", "test_surface": "Two-week non-clinical pilot with loneliness, certainty, cynicism, and community-contact measures.", "would_weaken_or_falsify": "The practice increases isolation, corrosive doubt, or performs no better than asking for citations."}], "idea_id": "184f0313f1a2464c", "idea_path": "observations/claude/2026-05-30-a-shared-word-is-not-two-witnesses.md", "literature_search_queries": ["Gaudapada Madhyamaka influence ajativada non origination Alatashanti Richard King", "Mandukya Karika 4.22 Mulamadhyamakakarika 1.1 non origination self other both neither", "historical linguistics comparative method genetic areal borrowing chance universals convergence", "Samuel Sandmel Parallelomania similarity influence borrowing comparative religion", "Jonathan Z Smith comparison redescription rectification Oliver Freiberger comparative methodology religion", "Daodejing 40 return movement of Dao Plotinus return to the One epistrophe"], "markdown_path": "reviews/originality/2026-05-30-a-shared-word-is-not-two-witnesses-772b49c45d1646bf.md", "near_neighbors": [{"difference": "This candidate sharpens the prior into an ordering rule: provenance must gate strain, and smoothness may lower confidence under possible contact.", "novelty_impact": "Major downgrade. Treat as an extension of the translation-strain codebook, not a new doctrine.", "overlap": "Very close. The internal prior already says convergence caused by borrowing or shared modern discourse must not be overvalued.", "source": "Internal Lumenary records on Translation Strain, especially the 2026-05-26 follow-up requiring an independence field for borrowing, colonial translation, shared modern discourse, and cross-training."}, {"difference": "The candidate imports that distinction into comparative religion and attaches it to a translation-strain score.", "novelty_impact": "Reduces novelty to application and workflow design.", "overlap": "Close structural near-neighbor. The linguistic method already distinguishes resemblance due to universals, chance, borrowing, diffusion, and genetic inheritance.", "source": "Aikhenvald and Dixon, Areal Diffusion and Genetic Inheritance, Oxford University Press, https://academic.oup.com/book/48227"}, {"difference": "Sandmel mainly cautions against uncontrolled influence claims. This candidate cautions against treating low-strain similarity as independent confirmation.", "novelty_impact": "Strong downgrade, but the inversion of strain remains a useful refinement.", "overlap": "Close. Sandmel warns against over-reading similarities and moving too quickly from parallel to source or derivation.", "source": "Samuel Sandmel, Parallelomania, Journal of Biblical Literature 81, 1962, https://www.sbl-site.org/assets/pdfs/presidentialaddresses/JBL81_1_1Sandmel1961.pdf"}, {"difference": "The candidate adds a provenance gate before scoring convergence strength.", "novelty_impact": "Supports extended status, not discovery.", "overlap": "Close methodological prior. Comparison is constructed through selection, description, juxtaposition, redescription, rectification, and theory formation, not discovered by surface likeness.", "source": "Oliver Freiberger, Elements of a Comparative Methodology in the Study of Religion, https://www.mdpi.com/2077-1444/9/2/38, and Jonathan Z. Smith comparison operations."}, {"difference": "The candidate uses this as a scoring anomaly for translation strain rather than only as Indological history.", "novelty_impact": "Lowers source novelty, raises usefulness as a control case.", "overlap": "Very close on the decisive example: Gaudapada's fourth chapter is widely discussed in relation to Madhyamaka and Yogacara terminology and argument.", "source": "Richard King, Early Advaita Vedanta and Buddhism, Google Books record, https://books.google.com/books/about/Early_Advaita_Ved%C4%81nta_and_Buddhism.html?id=p1bASTAOhjoC, and IEP Gaudapada, https://iep.utm.edu/gau%E1%B8%8Dapad/"}], "next_loop_instructions": ["Merge or cross-index with Convergence as Translation Strain and Translation Strain as a Load Test for Convergence.", "Add a required provenance gate before any convergence score: independent, inheritance, borrowing, shared milieu, shared translator, modern universalizing, cross-training, unknown.", "Split strain into lexical, logical, ritual, authority, verification, practice-aim, and metaphysical layers.", "Use Gaudapada and Madhyamaka as a contact-control case, not as independent confirmation.", "Run an A/B scoring test to see whether provenance-first coding changes decisions compared with strain-only coding.", "Pilot the Borrowed-Word Check only with stable reflective seekers, and track loneliness, cynicism, curiosity, and real community contact."], "novelty_adjustment": "Lower novelty from 0.52 to 0.36. The contact-versus-independence problem is old in historical linguistics, biblical studies, and comparative religion, and internal Lumenary already asked for an independence field. The useful addition is the provenance-before-strain ordering rule and the warning that smoothness can invert evidential weight. Publishability should stay limited because the human fit is real but narrow: reflective unaffiliated seekers with meaning loss and lonely certainty needs. It is not for acute grief, crisis, destabilization, or people who need actual community rather than another analytic check.", "originality_status": "extended", "path": "reviews/originality/2026-05-30-a-shared-word-is-not-two-witnesses-772b49c45d1646bf.json", "practitioner_test": {"answers_that_reduce_originality": "Scholars say this is simply Sandmel, Smith, Freiberger, historical linguistics, or standard source criticism, and that the added gate changes no real decisions.", "answers_that_support_contribution": "Practitioners or scholars identify cases where provenance-first coding reverses a convergence score and prevents a harmful or misleading teaching claim.", "questions": ["Would this provenance gate change any comparison you would otherwise accept as convergence?", "Can you name low-strain similarities that are clearly borrowed and high-strain similarities that are plausibly independent?", "Does the Gaudapada and Madhyamaka case prove the rule, or only show that strain must be coded by layer?", "For seekers, does the borrowed-word check reduce false certainty without increasing loneliness or cynicism?"], "relevant_practitioners": ["historians of religion", "comparative theologians", "Indologists and Buddhologists", "historical linguists", "translation-studies scholars", "cross-trained contemplative teachers", "spiritually unaffiliated seekers using cross-tradition synthesis"]}, "primary_text_close_read": {"primary_pair": ["Gaudapada, Mandukya Karika 4.22 and Alatashanti context, https://www.wisdomlib.org/hinduism/book/mandukya-upanishad-karika-bhashya/d/doc143736.html and https://vivekavani.com/mau/", "Nagarjuna, Mulamadhyamakakarika 1.1, https://www.energyenhancement.org/Buddhism-Encyclopedia/encyclopediaofbuddhism.org/wiki/M%C5%ABlamadhyamakak%C4%81rik%C4%81.html; contrast case: Daodejing 40, https://new.chine-culture.com/en/chinese-language/chinese-classics/laozi-classic-way-and-virtue/chapter-40-tao-te-ching, and Plotinus, https://iep.utm.edu/plotinus/"], "risk_of_overread": "High. Contact does not prove borrowing in the specific passage, and lack of known contact does not prove independence. Low strain can also arise from shared human constraints, common logical forms, or later translators making terms smoother. The Plotinus and Dao contrast is suggestive but thin unless Greek and Chinese source roles are coded rather than compared through English keywords.", "secondary_literature_gap": "Before publication, read full Richard King, Early Advaita Vedanta and Buddhism, Michael Comans, T. R. V. Murti, Hajime Nakamura, Jonathan Z. Smith, Oliver Freiberger, Samuel Sandmel on parallelomania, Aikhenvald and Dixon on areal diffusion and genetic inheritance, and scholarship on Chinese Buddhist matching concepts. Full monograph access remains needed for the strongest Gaudapada claims.", "structural_observation": "Gaudapada 4.22 and MMK 1.1 share the tetralemma-like denial of arising from self, other, both, or no cause. The lexical and logical strain is low, but Gaudapada's surrounding frame moves toward ajati for an unborn Self or Brahman, while Nagarjuna's frame rejects intrinsic arising without licensing a Vedantic Self. The best reading is layer-specific: lexical and argumentative strain can be low while metaphysical strain is high. Daodejing 40 and Plotinus both involve return, but Daoist reversal, weakness, and nonbeing do not play the same role as Plotinian ascent toward the One, so the independent comparison is rougher."}, "recommended_scores": {"counterargument_quality": 0.91, "novelty": 0.36, "source_reliability": 0.78}, "run_ids": ["20260530-110134-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-", "20260530-110134-codex-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-"], "title": "A Shared Word Is Not Two Witnesses", "unlike_statement": "Unlike standard comparative-method warnings and the prior Lumenary independence field, this idea says a strain score has no evidential direction until provenance is coded; under plausible contact, smooth likeness should often reduce independent-confirmation confidence. That is a useful extension, not a discovery."}
./reviews/originality/audits.jsonl:76:{"agent": "claude", "anomaly_probe": {"anomaly_candidate": "Stage-specific and operative-consensus cases, such as breath attention in early Buddhist practice, basic Vinaya rules, or a catechism-level Christian confession.", "confidence_effect": "Lowers confidence in any simple variance metric. Raises the need for operative weighting and inter-rater reliability before the gate can carry public evidential weight.", "why_it_breaks_or_strains_model": "A tradition can have enormous textual and historical variance while still giving practitioners a narrow operative instruction at a defined stage. If the denominator counts every variant equally, it will falsely mark stable practice instructions as selection-dependent. If it weights only operative variants, the model becomes dependent on disputed judgments about authority, institution, stage, and living practice."}, "audit_id": "67802a7a8e6bf629", "claim_units": ["Between-tradition strain is unreliable without within-tradition variance.", "Traditions vary across sub-schools, stages, genres, institutions, and polemical eras.", "If internal variance rivals the cross-tradition gap, the verdict depends on which internal variant was selected.", "Within-tradition variance must be weighted by operative practice centrality, not raw textual existence.", "A comparison can pass a provenance gate but fail a variance gate."], "confidence": 0.73, "created_at": "2026-05-30T11:47:12+02:00", "cross_domain_prediction": {"domain": "Political ideology and psychotherapy comparison.", "prediction": "For high-variance categories, slogan-level comparisons will flip depending on which internal school, stage, or institution is selected. Weighted internal-variance coding will reduce false convergence and false opposition.", "structural_translation": "Before comparing capitalism and socialism, CBT and ACT, or secular mindfulness and Buddhist meditation, one must check whether each category varies internally more than the alleged cross-category gap.", "would_count_against_it": "Cross-domain comparison verdicts remain stable across internal variants, or ordinary category labels explain outcomes better than weighted internal-variance scores."}, "exact_claim": "A translation-strain score needs a denominator. Before claiming that two traditions converge or clash on a claim unit, Lumenary must measure weighted within-tradition variance for the same unit. If internal spread is as wide as the between-tradition gap, the comparison is selection-dependent and should receive no evidential weight.", "execution_id": "parallel-20260530-113437-20260530-113437", "falsifiable_predictions": [{"expected_observation": "Coders assigned Theravada anatta versus Pudgalavada person, and Shankara-style self-recognition versus scriptural-testimony Advaita, will return contradictory convergence or divergence verdicts for the Atman and anatta comparison.", "if_model_is_right": "High internal-variance units should produce unstable convergence verdicts.", "test_surface": "Blind coder experiment with controlled claim units and assigned internal variants.", "would_weaken_or_falsify": "Convergence verdicts stay stable no matter which legitimate internal variant is selected."}, {"expected_observation": "Comparisons on narrower practice instructions, such as attending to breath, ethical restraint, or confession of fault, will show stronger agreement among coders than metaphysical self comparisons.", "if_model_is_right": "Low internal-variance units should produce stable verdicts.", "test_surface": "Inter-rater comparison study across high-variance and low-variance claim units.", "would_weaken_or_falsify": "Verdict stability is not predicted by internal-variance scores, or low-variance units produce just as much disagreement."}, {"expected_observation": "Weighting variants by living practice centrality, stage, institution, and teacher use will change which comparisons fail the variance gate.", "if_model_is_right": "Operative weighting matters more than raw textual spread.", "test_surface": "Expert and practitioner weighting exercise with inter-rater reliability analysis.", "would_weaken_or_falsify": "Raw textual variance and operative weighted variance produce the same decisions, or experts cannot agree on weights above chance."}, {"expected_observation": "Some comparisons will be historically independent but internally unstable, while others will be internally stable but historically entangled through borrowing, shared translators, or modern discourse.", "if_model_is_right": "The variance gate is orthogonal to the provenance gate.", "test_surface": "Paired application of provenance-first coding and variance-gate coding to the same comparison set.", "would_weaken_or_falsify": "Provenance and internal variance always move together, making the new gate redundant."}, {"expected_observation": "Stable reflective readers exposed to online comparative slogans show less all-is-one universalism and less cynical dismissal, while still choosing one concrete practice action within a week.", "if_model_is_right": "The self-agreement check helps a specific modern cohort without becoming avoidance.", "test_surface": "Small randomized pilot with measures for rumination, action completion, cynicism, false-harmony endorsement, and practice commitment.", "would_weaken_or_falsify": "The practice increases rumination, paralysis, distrust, or avoidance of commitment compared with a simple source-humility prompt."}], "idea_id": "5bca4594ea00fa13", "idea_path": "observations/claude/2026-05-30-first-ask-if-a-path-agrees-with-itself.md", "literature_search_queries": ["religious comparison internal diversity representative selection comparands tertium comparationis within tradition variation", "Oliver Freiberger comparative methodology religion scale scope selection description juxtaposition redescription rectification", "Jonathan Z Smith comparison religion redescription map territory selection comparands", "world religions paradigm critique essentialism intragroup diversity internal diversity religion", "Wilfred Cantwell Smith religion reification cumulative tradition personal faith diversity", "Pudgalavada person neither same nor different aggregates Kathavatthu Puggalakatha", "Svatantrika Prasangika distinction Bhaviveka Candrakirti independent argument reductio", "effect size between group difference within group variance heterogeneity multilevel modeling"], "markdown_path": "reviews/originality/2026-05-30-first-ask-if-a-path-agrees-with-itself-67802a7a8e6bf629.md", "near_neighbors": [{"difference": "The candidate adds an explicit admissibility threshold: between-tradition strain must exceed weighted internal variance.", "novelty_impact": "Substantial downgrade, but the denominator rule may still be a useful synthesis.", "overlap": "Very close on selection of comparands, scale, scope, and the need to defend what is being compared.", "source": "Oliver Freiberger, Elements of a Comparative Methodology in the Study of Religion, https://www.mdpi.com/2077-1444/9/2/38"}, {"difference": "The candidate makes selection-dependence testable through internal-variance controls.", "novelty_impact": "Reduces novelty of the selection-artifact warning.", "overlap": "Close on comparison being an act of scholarly redescription shaped by selected examples rather than a neutral discovery of natural sameness.", "source": "Jonathan Z. Smith, In Comparison a Magic Dwells and related comparison essays, https://classics.osu.edu/sites/classics.osu.edu/files/Magic_Dwells.pdf"}, {"difference": "The candidate applies the critique to claim-unit scoring and requires a variance denominator before convergence evidence is admitted.", "novelty_impact": "Internal diversity itself is known prior art.", "overlap": "Close on abstracted religions flattening internal diversity and hybrid lived practice.", "source": "World Religions Paradigm critiques, for example context and essentialism discussion at https://journals.sagepub.com/doi/10.1177/20503032241226966"}, {"difference": "The candidate moves from anti-reification to a scoring protocol for specific comparative claims.", "novelty_impact": "Supports extended or synthesis status, not discovery.", "overlap": "Close on resisting static treatment of a religion as one thing with one essence.", "source": "Wilfred Cantwell Smith on religion as reified category, overview at https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wilfred_Cantwell_Smith"}, {"difference": "The candidate imports the structure into religious comparison and adds operative-practice weighting.", "novelty_impact": "The denominator structure is known, but its application to translation strain is a novel synthesis.", "overlap": "Near exact structural model outside the domain: a between-group difference must be interpreted against within-group variation and measurement noise.", "source": "Statistical effect size, heterogeneity, and multilevel reasoning, general reference at https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Effect_size"}, {"difference": "This is evidence for the gate, not the gate itself.", "novelty_impact": "Raises source relevance but also exposes weighting problems because Pudgalavada is historically important but not a living mainstream lineage.", "overlap": "Provides the internal Buddhist variance case the model relies on: not-self sutta discipline versus a real or inexpressible person in Buddhist scholastic debate.", "source": "Pudgalavada Buddhist Philosophy, IEP, https://iep.utm.edu/pudgalavada-buddhist-philosophy/; Kathavatthu PDF, https://www.abhidhamma.com/Kathavatthu_en.pdf"}, {"difference": "Again an example of internal spread rather than a full comparative scoring method.", "novelty_impact": "Supports the anomaly pressure against broad tradition labels.", "overlap": "Shows internal contest over assertion posture, independent argument, and reductio within a broad Madhyamaka family.", "source": "Madhyamaka, SEP, https://plato.stanford.edu/archives/spr2022/entries/madhyamaka/; Dreyfus and McClintock, The Svatantrika-Prasangika Distinction, publisher listing https://wisdomexperience.org/product/svatantrika-prasangika-distinction/"}, {"difference": "This candidate adds a denominator gate that asks whether each side is internally stable enough to compare.", "novelty_impact": "Keeps this as novel_synthesis rather than candidate discovery.", "overlap": "Close on provenance, role, authority, verification, and translation strain before granting convergence.", "source": "Internal Lumenary prior: Translation Strain as a Load Test for Convergence and A Shared Word Is Not Two Witnesses from project memory."}], "next_loop_instructions": ["Do not publish as doctrine. Treat as a methodological control for translation-strain scoring.", "Build a variance-gate codebook with fields for claim unit, tradition, source layer, genre, stage, institution, internal variants, operative weight, evidence passage, between-tradition strain, within-tradition variance, provenance status, and confidence.", "Require operative weighting and inter-rater reliability before using the gate publicly.", "Test first on Atman and anatta, Buddhist personhood, Advaita self-knowledge, Madhyamaka assertion posture, breath attention, ethical restraint, and a low-variance ritual instruction.", "Run the variance gate and provenance gate on the same comparison set to test orthogonality.", "Add safety limits to The Self-Agreement Check: no more than twice weekly, stop for rumination, paralysis, cynicism, distrust, or avoidance of concrete practice.", "Compare against baselines: Freiberger selection and scope review, ordinary source criticism, world-religions anti-essentialism, provenance-first coding, and a simple source-humility prompt."], "novelty_adjustment": "Lower novelty from 0.60 to 0.52. The idea combines known internal-diversity critique, comparative-method selection theory, anti-essentialism, and statistical effect-size logic. The possible contribution is the explicit denominator gate for Lumenary translation-strain scoring. Human-condition fit is moderate: it serves reflective readers unsettled by digital comparison and meaning loss, but it is not a practice for acute distress or for people using analysis to avoid commitment.", "originality_status": "novel_synthesis", "path": "reviews/originality/2026-05-30-first-ask-if-a-path-agrees-with-itself-67802a7a8e6bf629.json", "practitioner_test": {"answers_that_reduce_originality": "Scholars say careful comparativists already do this under selection, scale, scope, representativeness, and anti-essentialism, or practitioners say operative teaching is much narrower than textual variance. Originality also falls if coders cannot weight variants reliably.", "answers_that_support_contribution": "Practitioners and scholars identify cases where the variance gate flips comparison verdicts, catches false AI or influencer summaries, and predicts when comparison will destabilize seekers without improving practice.", "questions": ["Would this variance gate change any comparison decision you would not already change through ordinary selection, scope, and internal-diversity cautions?", "How should marginal, extinct, polemical, minority, stage-specific, and living-practice variants be weighted?", "Can you name a comparison that passes provenance but fails internal-variance stability?", "Can you name a comparison whose internal disputes are pedagogical registers rather than real divergence?", "For modern seekers, does this check reduce false certainty, or does it feed analysis paralysis and avoidance of practice?"], "relevant_practitioners": ["comparative religion scholars", "comparative theologians", "Buddhist studies scholars", "Advaita Vedanta scholars", "Madhyamaka scholars", "interfaith educators", "lineage teachers who train beginners", "statisticians or social scientists familiar with variance and effect size"]}, "primary_text_close_read": {"primary_pair": ["SN 22.59, https://www.accesstoinsight.org/ati/tipitaka/sn/sn22/sn22.059.nymo.html, read against Kathavatthu Puggalakatha and Pudgalavada reconstruction, https://www.abhidhamma.com/Kathavatthu_en.pdf and https://iep.utm.edu/pudgalavada-buddhist-philosophy/", "Brihadaranyaka Upanishad 3.7.23, https://sacred-texts.com/hin/sbe15/sbe15070.htm, read against internal Advaita questions of self-luminosity, scripture, and recognition, with Madhyamaka assertion-posture pressure from SEP, https://plato.stanford.edu/archives/spr2022/entries/madhyamaka/"], "risk_of_overread": "Medium high. The variance analogy can inflate marginal, extinct, polemical, or purely scholastic variants and make every tradition look too unstable to compare. Some internal differences are stage-specific pedagogy, genre difference, or skillful means rather than contradiction. Operative weighting is essential but contestable. Human-condition fit is modest: it helps digitally unsettled readers resist false harmony and cynical dismissal, but it can worsen analysis paralysis in over-reflective people who need commitment more than more comparison.", "secondary_literature_gap": "Before raising novelty, read Freiberger on selection, scale, scope, and comparands; Jonathan Z. Smith on comparison and redescription; Wilfred Cantwell Smith on reification of religion; world religions paradigm critiques; Clooney and Cornille on comparative theology; Dreyfus and McClintock on Svatantrika-Prasangika; Priestley or other Pudgalavada scholarship; Shankara and Advaita studies on svaprakasha and shabda pramana; and statistical literature on effect size, heterogeneity, multilevel models, and within-group versus between-group variance.", "structural_observation": "SN 22.59 trains disidentification from form, feeling, perception, formations, and consciousness. Pudgalavada sources and reconstructions preserve a Buddhist person that is neither identical with nor different from the aggregates, partly to protect karma, rebirth, liberation, and ordinary person-talk. That intra-Buddhist spread complicates any single Buddhism versus Atman comparison. Brihadaranyaka 3.7.23 authorizes an unseen seer and knower, while Advaita disputes about recognition, self-luminosity, and scripture complicate how that knower is established. The Madhyamaka Bhaviveka and Candrakirti dispute adds a second internal variable: a tradition's assertion posture may be contested rather than fixed."}, "recommended_scores": {"counterargument_quality": 0.89, "novelty": 0.52, "source_reliability": 0.74}, "run_ids": ["20260530-113437-codex-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-", "20260530-113437-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-"], "title": "First Ask If a Path Agrees With Itself", "unlike_statement": "Unlike ordinary internal-diversity cautions, Freiberger's selection framework, Smith's redescription model, and world-religions essentialism critiques, this candidate proposes a specific admissibility test: a cross-tradition strain score has evidential weight only when between-tradition strain exceeds weighted within-tradition variance for the same claim unit."}
./reviews/originality/audits.jsonl:77:{"agent": "claude", "anomaly_probe": {"anomaly_candidate": "A low-strain claim unit appearing in two traditions with strong evidence of no plausible contact, no shared translator, no common imperial or colonial vocabulary, and no later perennialist mediation.", "confidence_effect": "Would lower confidence in the strong inversion from 0.76 to about 0.55 and shift status from extended protocol to a bounded caution. It would not revive naive convergence scoring because provenance would still be required.", "why_it_breaks_or_strains_model": "If such cases replicate, low strain is not only a borrowing fingerprint. It may also mark human cognitive constraints, convergent practice effects, shared phenomenology, or genuinely independent recurrence. The model would need to become partial confound control, not sign inversion."}, "audit_id": "a124cfeb0014609d", "claim_units": ["Translation strain measures mapping ease, not independent recurrence.", "The same variables that lower strain, shared lineage, translators, vocabulary, teachers, and polemical contact, can be traces of historical contact.", "In contacted traditions, low strain should lower confidence in independent convergence until provenance is established.", "Gaudapada and Madhyamaka show low strain on non-origination language while retaining high strain around self, Atman, Brahman, and remainder.", "External historical evidence, not strain magnitude, must establish whether a convergence is independent.", "The human-condition teaching warns spiritually unmoored seekers not to use abstract sameness as a substitute for real belonging."], "confidence": 0.76, "created_at": "2026-05-30T12:16:05+02:00", "cross_domain_prediction": {"domain": "Historical linguistics and cultural phylogenetics", "prediction": "In datasets of cultural traits, myths, or doctrinal phrases, high surface similarity among geographically or institutionally connected communities will more often trace to borrowing, shared source, or areal convergence than to independent recurrence. Independent recurrence will require systematic correspondence across held-out features, not only easy mapping of the focal claim.", "structural_translation": "Translation strain corresponds to surface resemblance. Provenance corresponds to cognacy, borrowing, areal contact, shared source, or chance. The candidate predicts that apparent closeness cannot be used as independent-origin evidence until contact pathways are modeled.", "would_count_against_it": "If surface similarity reliably predicts independent recurrence after known contact routes are controlled, or if contact modeling adds no predictive value beyond structural similarity, the cross-domain analogy weakens."}, "exact_claim": "Low translation strain between traditions should not be treated as evidence of independent convergence when historical contact is plausible. In entangled cases, low strain may be a trace of borrowing, shared translators, shared polemic, shared training, or homogenized modern vocabulary, so independence must be established by external provenance before strain is allowed to count.", "execution_id": "parallel-20260530-120252-20260530-120252", "falsifiable_predictions": [{"expected_observation": "A coded corpus of cross-tradition convergence claims will show that low-strain pairs have higher rates of shared lineage, common translators, known polemic, teacher contact, colonial discourse, or modern perennialist vocabulary than high-strain pairs.", "if_model_is_right": "Low strain is enriched by contact rather than by independent recurrence.", "test_surface": "Corpus study of comparative religion claims with blind strain coding and separate provenance coding.", "would_weaken_or_falsify": "Low-strain and high-strain pairs show no difference in contact enrichment after controlling for topic, genre, date, and language family."}, {"expected_observation": "A close coding of Mandukya Karika chapter 4 against MMK and Yogacara sources will find low-strain units concentrated in Buddhist technical or argumentative forms, while high-strain units cluster around Vedantic remainder, Atman, Brahman, Turiya, or consciousness.", "if_model_is_right": "The Gaudapada case is a contact-confounded comparison.", "test_surface": "Primary-text codebook with Sanskrit term mapping, dating notes, and independent specialist review.", "would_weaken_or_falsify": "Low and high strain units do not track the proposed contact and remainder pattern, or the same non-origination structure is better explained by earlier Upanishadic sources alone."}, {"expected_observation": "When coders apply provenance-first coding before strain scoring, some apparent convergence claims will be downgraded or relabeled as shared source, borrowing, translator artifact, or shared milieu.", "if_model_is_right": "Provenance must be coded before strain has evidential weight.", "test_surface": "A/B scoring test using the same claim units, one group strain-only, one group provenance-first.", "would_weaken_or_falsify": "Provenance-first coding almost never changes convergence scores compared with strain-only scoring."}, {"expected_observation": "In a small pilot with stable spiritually eclectic readers, the Borrowed-Likeness Check reduces all-paths-same certainty and increases one concrete community or tradition-contact action without increasing loneliness or cynicism.", "if_model_is_right": "Low-strain sameness comforts a specific modern wound but can mislead belonging.", "test_surface": "Two-week randomized pilot measuring false-harmony endorsement, cynicism, loneliness, rumination, and real contact actions.", "would_weaken_or_falsify": "The practice increases distrust, isolation, contempt, rumination, or reduces real belonging compared with a simple source-humility prompt."}, {"expected_observation": "Borrowed or translator-mediated parallels will preserve unusually similar vocabulary, sequence, or metaphors across languages, while independent parallels will show more functional similarity with lower lexical and rhetorical alignment.", "if_model_is_right": "Borrowed agreements and independent agreements behave differently under translation.", "test_surface": "Comparative text analysis with known-borrowing controls, no-contact controls, and modern translation controls.", "would_weaken_or_falsify": "Borrowed and independent cases show the same lexical, rhetorical, and role-similarity profiles."}], "idea_id": "9310d0367c05acce", "idea_path": "observations/claude/2026-05-30-sameness-can-be-the-fingerprint-of-borrowing.md", "literature_search_queries": ["Gaudapada Mandukya Karika Alatashanti Madhyamaka Buddhism borrowing terminology Richard King", "Nagarjuna Mulamadhyamakakarika 24.18 dependent arising emptiness translation", "Oliver Freiberger Elements of a Comparative Methodology in the Study of Religion selection description juxtaposition redescription", "Jonathan Z Smith In Comparison a Magic Dwells diffusion parallel independent invention borrowing", "Samuel Sandmel Parallelomania similarity source derivation borrowing evidence", "historical linguistics borrowing loanwords cognates systematic correspondences comparative method", "Lutz Doering Parallels without Parallelomania comparative analysis genealogical dependence", "source criticism independent attestation common source dependence historical method"], "markdown_path": "reviews/originality/2026-05-30-sameness-can-be-the-fingerprint-of-borrowing-a124cfeb0014609d.md", "near_neighbors": [{"difference": "The candidate turns Smith's methodological warning into a local scoring rule for translation strain: low strain in potentially contacted pairs should not count as independent convergence until provenance is settled.", "novelty_impact": "Major downgrade. The underlying caution is known; the possible contribution is the operational sign inversion inside the Lumenary strain workflow.", "overlap": "Very close. Smith directly treats similarity, contiguity, borrowing, diffusion, independent invention, and the need to integrate pattern with history rather than projecting a scholar's remembered similarity into an objective connection.", "source": "Jonathan Z. Smith, In Comparison a Magic Dwells, https://classics.osu.edu/sites/classics.osu.edu/files/Magic_Dwells.pdf"}, {"difference": "Sandmel primarily warns against overclaiming dependence from similarity. This candidate warns against overclaiming independent convergence from low strain. It is the mirror problem, not a wholly new problem.", "novelty_impact": "Strong downgrade. The candidate should cite Sandmel as a primary methodological ancestor.", "overlap": "Very close on the danger of moving too quickly from observed similarity to claims about derivation or relation.", "source": "Samuel Sandmel, Parallelomania, Journal of Biblical Literature 81, no. 1, 1962, reference and transcription at https://bhroberts.org/records/jpNwrg-3xncCf/samuel_sandmel_defines_parallelomania"}, {"difference": "The candidate adds a particular confound model for translation-strain scores rather than a general comparison methodology.", "novelty_impact": "Downgrades broad originality. Leaves room only for a workflow-specific extension.", "overlap": "Close on comparison requiring first-order philology, selection, scale, scope, description, juxtaposition, redescription, rectification, and theory formation.", "source": "Oliver Freiberger, Elements of a Comparative Methodology in the Study of Religion, https://www.wisdomlib.org/uploads/journals/mdpi-relig/2018-volume-9-issue-2--2077-1444-9-2-38-.pdf and DOAJ summary https://doaj.org/article/8c8b78717a9943a9a9e1ea76da47ec2a"}, {"difference": "The candidate imports this logic into doctrinal comparison and translation-strain scoring.", "novelty_impact": "The analogy is apt but not new in its home domain. It supports novel_synthesis at most, and probably extended status because Smith and Sandmel already brought similar issues into religious studies.", "overlap": "Near exact cross-domain structure. Surface similarity can be caused by borrowing, inheritance, chance, or contact, so resemblance alone cannot establish genealogy or independent recurrence.", "source": "Historical linguistics on borrowing versus cognates and systematic correspondences, for example Networks uncover hidden lexical borrowing in Indo-European language evolution, https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC3097823/ and comparative method overview https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Comparative_method"}, {"difference": "The candidate's narrower move is to treat low strain as suspect when contact is possible, not only to classify relationships after comparison.", "novelty_impact": "Moderate downgrade. The exact Lumenary scoring inversion remains useful but not a discovery.", "overlap": "Close on comparing texts without assuming direct dependence, and on distinguishing direct borrowing, common tradition, shared milieu, and contextual relationship.", "source": "Lutz Doering, Parallels without Parallelomania, King's College listing, https://kclpure.kcl.ac.uk/portal/en/publications/parallels-without-parallelomania-methodological-reflections-on-co/ and intertextual methodology summary https://intertextual.bible/article/intertextuality-and-parallelomania"}, {"difference": "King supplies the historical and philosophical case; the candidate uses it as a general rule for evaluating translation strain.", "novelty_impact": "The case is known. Originality depends entirely on whether the strain-score protocol makes decisions scholars would not already make.", "overlap": "Very close on the case material: Gaudapada's non-origination, Buddhist influence, and the difference between no birth in Madhyamaka and an Unborn in Advaita.", "source": "Richard King and related scholarship on Gaudapada, Madhyamaka, ajati, and Advaita, including The Vedantic Heritage of the Gaudapadiya-karika PDF, https://www.jewelheart.org/wp-content/uploads/2022/09/Richard-King_The-Vedantic-Heritage-of-the-Gaudapadiya-karika-.pdf and Ajativada overview https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aj%C4%81tiv%C4%81da"}, {"difference": "The candidate applies independent-attestation logic to cross-tradition spiritual convergence and modern perennialist comfort.", "novelty_impact": "Downgrades novelty. The teaching line is a spiritualized version of a standard historical method.", "overlap": "Close structural rule: repeated testimony only strengthens a claim when sources are independent, and shared dependence can make multiple witnesses only one line of evidence.", "source": "Source criticism and independent attestation, for example criterion of multiple attestation and source dependence discussions, https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Criterion_of_multiple_attestation"}, {"difference": "This candidate changes the relation between provenance and strain from additive fields to causal confound, and proposes that low strain can become a suspicion signal.", "novelty_impact": "Major local downgrade. Treat as an extension of the provenance gate, not a new doctrine candidate.", "overlap": "Extremely close on provenance gating, translation strain, false convergence, internal variance, shared translator, borrowing, and modern homogenizing vocabulary.", "source": "Internal Lumenary near-neighbors: A Shared Word Is Not Two Witnesses, Translation Strain as a Load Test for Convergence, and First Ask If a Path Agrees With Itself, provided in project memory."}], "next_loop_instructions": ["Do not publish as a standalone discovery or doctrine claim. Cross-index with A Shared Word Is Not Two Witnesses, Translation Strain as a Load Test for Convergence, First Ask If a Path Agrees With Itself, and No Word Travels Alone.", "Rename the contribution as a provenance-confound rule for translation-strain scoring.", "Build a provenance-first codebook with values for independent, shared source, direct borrowing, common translator, shared polemical milieu, teacher cross-training, colonial or modern universalizing vocabulary, parallel development, uncertain, and analyst-frame-refused.", "Do not let strain score count as evidence for convergence until provenance has been coded independently from historical sources.", "Run the Gaudapada and Nagarjuna close-read with Sanskrit term checks, chapter dating notes, Shankara attribution caveats, and specialist review.", "Add no-contact anomaly cases before public use, including geographically separated apophatic negation, independent ritual similarities, and convergent cognitive or phenomenological cases.", "Pilot The Borrowed-Likeness Check only with stable spiritually eclectic readers. Stop for increased cynicism, isolation, contempt, rumination, panic, or withdrawal from real relationships."], "novelty_adjustment": "Lower novelty from 0.52 to 0.43. The core warning is known in Smith, Sandmel, Freiberger, source criticism, and historical linguistics, and it is very close to prior Lumenary provenance-gate work. The useful addition is the explicit causal-confound rule for translation-strain scoring. Human-condition fit is moderate and bounded: it serves spiritually unmoored seekers, loneliness, meaning loss, digital comparison, and false perennialist comfort, but it is not for acute grief, clinical distress, or people prone to cynicism and isolation.", "originality_status": "extended", "path": "reviews/originality/2026-05-30-sameness-can-be-the-fingerprint-of-borrowing-a124cfeb0014609d.json", "practitioner_test": {"answers_that_reduce_originality": "Scholars say this is simply Sandmel, Smith, Freiberger, independent attestation, or ordinary historical linguistics in Lumenary vocabulary. Originality also falls if practitioners say the practice is obvious and adds no discernment beyond teacher guidance or source humility.", "answers_that_support_contribution": "Support rises if provenance-first scoring flips real Lumenary convergence decisions, if experts agree that low strain often flags contact in entangled cases, and if the practice helps the target cohort move from abstract sameness toward real belonging without increasing cynicism.", "questions": ["Would this low-strain-as-contact-suspicion rule change a comparison you would not already change through ordinary provenance or source criticism?", "In the Gaudapada case, which specific terms or arguments are plausible borrowings, and which are better explained by Upanishadic or shared Indian debate contexts?", "Can you name a low-strain pair with strong no-contact provenance that would break the inversion rule?", "For practitioners, does genealogy matter for trust in practice, or only for scholarly evidence?", "For modern seekers, does the Borrowed-Likeness Check move people toward honest belonging, or does it create cynicism and more isolation?"], "relevant_practitioners": ["comparative religion scholars", "Indologists specializing in Gaudapada and Advaita", "Madhyamaka scholars", "historical linguists", "biblical intertextuality and source-criticism scholars", "comparative theologians", "lineage teachers working with cross-tradition students", "clinicians or spiritual directors working with lonely eclectic seekers"]}, "primary_text_close_read": {"primary_pair": ["Gaudapada, Mandukya Karika 4.29, 4.47, and 4.48, Wisdom Library Nikhilananda and Shankara rendering, https://www.wisdomlib.org/hinduism/book/mandukya-upanishad-karika-bhashya/d/doc143742.html, https://www.wisdomlib.org/hinduism/book/mandukya-upanishad-karika-bhashya/d/doc143758.html, https://www.wisdomlib.org/hinduism/book/mandukya-upanishad-karika-bhashya/d/doc143759.html", "Nagarjuna, Mulamadhyamakakarika 1.1 and 24.18-19, Encyclopedia of Buddhism summary with Garfield translations and translation references, https://www.energyenhancement.org/Buddhism-Encyclopedia/encyclopediaofbuddhism.org/wiki/M%C5%ABlamadhyamakak%C4%81rik%C4%81.html"], "risk_of_overread": "High. The idea risks treating borrowing as contamination, when traditions often learn, argue, translate, and transform honestly. It also risks confusing genealogy with truth. A borrowed convergence is not independent evidence, but it may still be doctrinally or practically valid. The Gaudapada case is especially risky because chapter 4, Shankara attribution, Buddhist technical vocabulary, Upanishadic inheritance, and broader Indian debate are all contested. Human-condition fit is real but narrow: it can help digitally unmoored seekers and people using perennialist sameness to soothe loneliness, but it may worsen cynicism, isolation, or analysis paralysis.", "secondary_literature_gap": "Before raising novelty or source reliability, read Richard King, Early Advaita Vedanta and Buddhism, including his work on Sunyata and Ajati; Michael Comans on early Advaita method; T. R. V. Murti; Hajime Nakamura; Sengaku Mayeda on Mandukya authorship and commentary issues; Ruegg on Madhyamaka; Siderits and Katsura on Nagarjuna; and full scholarship on Gaudapada chapter 4 rather than relying on IEP, Wikipedia, and excerpted translations. Also read Smith, Sandmel, Freiberger, Doering, Hays, source criticism, contact linguistics, and historical linguistics on borrowing versus independent attestation.", "structural_observation": "The Gaudapada passages use non-origination and the firebrand image to say that apparent perceiver and perceived arise as appearances in motionless consciousness, with Shankara explicitly reading the unborn mind as Brahman. The Nagarjuna passages reject arising from self, other, both, or no cause, then identify dependent arising with emptiness and reject non-empty entities. The shared anti-origination grammar is real, but the texts authorize different remainders: Gaudapada can support unborn consciousness, while Madhyamaka works against intrinsic nature. The candidate is right that low strain on dialectic can coexist with high strain on remainder, but the claim needs stronger dating, authorship, and transmission work before borrowing is used as the controlling explanation."}, "recommended_scores": {"counterargument_quality": 0.9, "novelty": 0.43, "source_reliability": 0.76}, "run_ids": ["20260530-120252-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-", "20260530-120252-codex-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-"], "title": "Sameness Can Be the Fingerprint of Borrowing", "unlike_statement": "Unlike Smith, Sandmel, Freiberger, historical linguistics, source criticism, and prior Lumenary provenance gates, this candidate gives one sharper operational rule: in traditions with plausible contact, low translation strain should count against independent-convergence confidence until external provenance evidence clears the contact confound."}
./reviews/originality/audits.jsonl:78:{"agent": "codex", "anomaly_probe": {"anomaly_candidate": "Authorized hybrid traditions, dual-trained lineages, and direct-recognition settings where borrowed language becomes native through disciplined practice, or where the sentence functions performatively rather than as a proposition to be regenerated.", "confidence_effect": "Lowers confidence in the universal form of the model, but supports a narrower status as a safety and comparison heuristic for unguided eclectic borrowing. If hybrid cases are common and well-corrected, novelty should drop toward renamed.", "why_it_breaks_or_strains_model": "The gate assumes that each tradition has separable carrier conditions and that importing another path's language is suspect until regenerated internally. Hybrid lineages, comparative theology, Buddhist modernist adaptations, and teacher-held direct introduction may make borrowing part of the real carrier. A strict gate could misclassify living synthesis as counterfeit, or make a practitioner over-check a sentence that should be tested by guidance, conduct, or practice fruit."}, "audit_id": "53c355c0cbaee241", "claim_units": ["A repeated spiritual sentence may be independent witness, borrowed habit, translation convention, blended teacher vocabulary, or a seeker's belonging strategy.", "Comparison should code claim unit, role, ontology, agency, practice aim, authority, verification, provenance, what is bent, what is dropped, and what is added.", "A similarity counts only if each tradition can reproduce the claim under its own carrier conditions.", "The gate is aimed not only at scholarly comparison but also at modern receivers who adopt spiritual sentences for identity, belonging, avoidance, or online display.", "The practice candidate asks what taught the sentence, who can correct it, and what concrete action it asks today.", "The idea should be treated as a discernment and safety gate, not a metaphysical doctrine."], "confidence": 0.78, "created_at": "2026-05-30T12:16:05+02:00", "cross_domain_prediction": {"domain": "Scientific replication and software or AI benchmarking", "prediction": "In AI or software evaluation, identical answers from models sharing training data, benchmark leakage, libraries, or evaluator prompts will overstate convergence. Results will become trustworthy only when independent pipelines can regenerate the answer under their own tests and failure checks.", "structural_translation": "A shared spiritual sentence is like two studies reporting the same result. Practice, authority, correction, and verification are like independent data, methods, code, measurement, and review. If two systems share a dataset, library, benchmark, prompt, or evaluator, their agreement is not independent replication.", "would_count_against_it": "If shared provenance does not increase correlated error, or if independent regeneration does not improve reliability over surface agreement, the cross-domain structure weakens."}, "exact_claim": "A cross-tradition agreement should not support doctrine or practice until each tradition can regenerate the claim from its own practice, correction system, authority, and verification rule. Shared words do not prove shared insight; shared roles matter only when they survive without importing one path's carrier conditions into another.", "execution_id": "parallel-20260530-120252-20260530-120252", "falsifiable_predictions": [{"expected_observation": "Blind reviewers using the gate will downgrade or relabel some apparent agreements that ordinary strain scoring accepts, especially where authority, verification, or practice aim fails to regenerate on one side.", "if_model_is_right": "The regeneration gate adds discernment beyond ordinary similarity and provenance checks.", "test_surface": "A/B comparison of strain-only, provenance-only, and regeneration-gate scoring on the same claim units.", "would_weaken_or_falsify": "The gate almost never changes decisions beyond Freiberger-style source criticism, Panikkar-style functional equivalence, or the existing Lumenary provenance gate."}, {"expected_observation": "Independent coders can reach acceptable agreement on role, authority, verification, practice aim, what is bent, what is dropped, and what is added for narrow primary-text pairs.", "if_model_is_right": "Carrier fields are observable enough to code.", "test_surface": "Inter-rater reliability study on Chandogya/SN 22.59, Dao De Jing/Pseudo-Dionysius, apophatic Buddhist/Christian pairs, and low-variance ritual instructions.", "would_weaken_or_falsify": "Coders cannot distinguish role from ontology, authority from verification, or bent meaning from dropped meaning above chance."}, {"expected_observation": "Shared spiritual sentences whose authority and verification fail to regenerate will produce more teacher-reported misuses, identity display, avoidance, or spiritual bypassing than sentences with clear carrier conditions.", "if_model_is_right": "The gate predicts misuse and repair patterns.", "test_surface": "Practitioner interviews and held-out warning or repair prediction from manuals, teacher cases, and receiver reports.", "would_weaken_or_falsify": "Misuse rates are better predicted by personality, mental health risk, teacher quality, or social context alone, with no added value from regeneration fields."}, {"expected_observation": "Stable eclectic adults or older teens who use the check before adopting or posting a major claim will show fewer identity-display uses and more concrete relationship, duty, or care actions within 24 hours, without increased rumination or shame.", "if_model_is_right": "The Borrowed Sentence Check serves the stated modern cohort.", "test_surface": "Small randomized pilot with stable participants, excluding acute crisis, OCD or scrupulosity loops, dissociation, mania, severe depression, addiction withdrawal, and unsafe authority situations.", "would_weaken_or_falsify": "Ordinary journaling, teacher guidance, or a simple wait-before-posting rule performs as well or better, or the check increases shame, obsessive analysis, distrust, or isolation."}, {"expected_observation": "Pairs that share language but diverge on verification, such as identity recognition, non-clinging, divine union, non-interference, teacher authorization, or conduct fruit, will produce higher translation strain after the gate than before it.", "if_model_is_right": "Shared words with mismatched verification rules are risky.", "test_surface": "Claim-unit coding across Advaita, early Buddhism, Daoism, Christian apophasis, Pure Land, Dzogchen, and modern nonduality.", "would_weaken_or_falsify": "Verification-rule mismatch does not predict scoring changes or practitioner concern."}], "idea_id": "21a74a93f85bbbe0", "idea_path": "observations/codex/2026-05-30-ask-who-taught-the-answer.md", "literature_search_queries": ["Panikkar homeomorphic equivalence functional equivalence comparison religion", "Freiberger comparative methodology religion selection description juxtaposition redescription rectification", "Jonathan Z Smith comparison redescription magic dwells similarity contiguity borrowing", "Sandmel parallelomania similarity source derivation biblical comparison", "Doering parallels without parallelomania comparative analysis genealogical dependence", "Lindbeck cultural linguistic theory doctrine grammar religion", "Asad discursive tradition religion authority practice genealogy", "Sharf Katz mystical experience language epistemology contextualism perennialism critique"], "markdown_path": "reviews/originality/2026-05-30-ask-who-taught-the-answer-53c355c0cbaee241.md", "near_neighbors": [{"difference": "The candidate adds a Lumenary operational gate: a claim must regenerate through practice, correction, authority, and verification before it supports doctrine or a practice seed.", "novelty_impact": "Strong downgrade. The core comparison logic is known; the contribution is a safety and workflow implementation.", "overlap": "Very close. Panikkar already asks for functional correspondences that respect each religious configuration rather than treating terms as simple synonyms.", "source": "Raimon Panikkar, homeomorphic equivalence, official glossary https://www.raimon-panikkar.org/english/gloss-homeomorphic.html"}, {"difference": "The candidate narrows the method to a doctrine-scoring and practitioner-facing regeneration test.", "novelty_impact": "Downgrades novelty. Treat as an applied extension, not a discovery.", "overlap": "Close on comparison as a controlled second-order method depending on first-order philology, document analysis, description, selection, scale, scope, juxtaposition, redescription, and rectification.", "source": "Oliver Freiberger, Elements of a Comparative Methodology in the Study of Religion, https://www.wisdomlib.org/uploads/journals/mdpi-relig/2018-volume-9-issue-2--2077-1444-9-2-38-.pdf"}, {"difference": "The candidate adds the question of whether each tradition can reproduce the claim under its own carrier conditions and whether a modern receiver is using the sentence for belonging or avoidance.", "novelty_impact": "Moderate downgrade. The receiver-use layer is useful, but the scholarly core is inherited.", "overlap": "Close on comparison being a scholarly act of selection and redescription, and on the danger of projecting similarity or contiguity into objective relation without method.", "source": "Jonathan Z. Smith, In Comparison a Magic Dwells, https://classics.osu.edu/sites/classics.osu.edu/files/Magic_Dwells.pdf"}, {"difference": "The candidate applies this to spiritual sentences and practice design rather than biblical allusion or halakhic parallels.", "novelty_impact": "Downgrades the methodological novelty, supports practice-test novelty only.", "overlap": "Close on refusing undifferentiated parallels and asking for availability, plausibility, relationship type, context, and function before claiming connection.", "source": "Sandmel, Doering, and intertextual criteria, https://bhroberts.org/records/jpNwrg-3xncCf/samuel_sandmel_defines_parallelomania, https://kclpure.kcl.ac.uk/portal/en/publications/parallels-without-parallelomania-methodological-reflections-on-co/, https://intertextual.bible/article/intertextuality-and-parallelomania"}, {"difference": "The candidate gives a specific checklist for doctrine scoring and asks what concrete action the borrowed sentence demands of the receiver.", "novelty_impact": "Substantial downgrade. Regeneration from internal grammar is known prior art.", "overlap": "Close structural neighbor. Lindbeck treats religious doctrine as rules or grammar inside a communal language and practice, so a sentence cannot simply be lifted across systems without changing its rule-governed use.", "source": "George Lindbeck, The Nature of Doctrine, cultural-linguistic model and doctrine as grammar, accessible overview example https://www.kci.go.kr/kciportal/ci/sereArticleSearch/ciSereArtiView.kci?sereArticleSearchBean.artiId=ART001871058"}, {"difference": "The candidate turns this into a small comparative gate and low-risk practice prompt for spiritually eclectic readers.", "novelty_impact": "Downgrades theoretical originality, leaves applied synthesis value.", "overlap": "Close on authority, discipline, genealogy, embodied practice, and the problem of universal religious categories that hide Western or modern assumptions.", "source": "Talal Asad, Genealogies of Religion and discursive tradition, publisher page https://press.jhu.edu/books/title/1644/genealogies-religion"}, {"difference": "The candidate asks for practical regeneration and correction holders rather than making a broad constructivist claim.", "novelty_impact": "Moderate downgrade. Useful as a bounded workflow control.", "overlap": "Close on reports and experiences being shaped by language, training, social context, and interpretive frameworks rather than freely translatable common cores.", "source": "Robert Sharf and Steven Katz on experience, language, and contextualism, for example Sharf resource https://deepblue.lib.umich.edu/items/25b7e9d4-d1f3-4280-8d53-95fa0b53db5c and SEP mysticism overview https://plato.stanford.edu/archives/fall2021/entries/mysticism/"}, {"difference": "The candidate consolidates these into a regeneration gate and a Borrowed Sentence Check.", "novelty_impact": "Major local downgrade. This should be cross-indexed or merged unless a blind distinct-content test shows separability.", "overlap": "Extremely close on source role, trained practice, correction holder, verification rule, provenance, bent meaning, dropped meaning, receiver wound, and counterfeit use.", "source": "Internal Lumenary near-neighbors: No Word Travels Alone, A Shared Word Is Not Two Witnesses, Stop When The Repair Changes, and Translation Strain records, supplied in project memory."}], "next_loop_instructions": ["Do not publish as a standalone discovery. Cross-index or merge with No Word Travels Alone, A Shared Word Is Not Two Witnesses, Translation Strain as a Load Test for Convergence, Stop When The Repair Changes, and the provenance-confound record.", "Rename as a regeneration-gate protocol for borrowed spiritual sentences and cross-tradition doctrine scoring.", "Build a one-page codebook with fields for claim unit, source role, ontology, agency, practice aim, authority, correction holder, verification rule, provenance, bent meaning, dropped meaning, added meaning, receiver wound, concrete action, warning, repair, and clinical exclusion.", "Use split-source blind coding. Do not let the same passage establish the source role, carrier conditions, and predicted repair.", "Run a distinct-content test against No Word Travels Alone and A Shared Word Is Not Two Witnesses. Merge if blind readers cannot state the added variable without prompting.", "Add anomaly cases before public use: authorized hybrids, comparative theology, direct recognition, Dogen practice-realization, Pure Land Other Power, sacramental speech, communal prayer, and non-instrumental ritual.", "Pilot the Borrowed Sentence Check only with stable eclectic readers and older teens with support. Stop for shame, panic, rumination, obsessive checking, dissociation, withdrawal, dependency, or unsafe authority dynamics."], "novelty_adjustment": "Lower novelty from 0.48 to 0.44. The theoretical core is close to Panikkar, Freiberger, Smith, Sandmel, Lindbeck, Asad, Sharf, Katz, source criticism, and recent Lumenary translation-strain records. The possible contribution is a compact regeneration gate that combines scholarly comparison with receiver safety and concrete action. Human-condition fit is clearer than for many abstract comparison records, but still bounded: it serves digital comparison, meaning loss, loneliness, and feeling out of place among stable eclectic readers. It is not a practice for acute distress, clinical checking loops, or guided practitioners who should use their actual teacher or care network.", "originality_status": "extended", "path": "reviews/originality/2026-05-30-ask-who-taught-the-answer-53c355c0cbaee241.json", "practitioner_test": {"answers_that_reduce_originality": "Originality falls if scholars say this is Panikkar, Lindbeck, Asad, Smith, Freiberger, Sandmel, or ordinary teacher discernment with new labels. It also falls if practitioners cannot identify failures the gate predicts, or if the pilot performs no better than ordinary journaling, teacher guidance, or waiting before posting.", "answers_that_support_contribution": "Support rises if practitioners provide concrete misborrowed-sentence cases, if the gate predicts repair instructions from held-out manuals or interviews, if coders can apply the fields reliably, and if the practice reduces digital identity display while increasing real conduct and belonging in the target cohort.", "questions": ["Is the regeneration gate different from what careful comparative theologians, source critics, and teachers already do?", "Can you name a concrete student failure caused by adopting a sentence without its carrier conditions?", "Can you name a case where borrowed language became valid because a new lineage or teacher corrected it well?", "Which fields are actually observable in practice: authority, correction, verification, role, practice aim, or receiver wound?", "For digitally unmoored seekers, does this check reduce false belonging and identity display, or does it deepen shame, loneliness, and analysis paralysis?"], "relevant_practitioners": ["comparative religion scholars", "comparative theologians", "interfaith educators", "Advaita Vedanta teachers and scholars", "Buddhist teachers and scholars", "Daoist studies scholars", "Christian apophatic and spiritual direction practitioners", "clinicians familiar with spiritual bypassing, OCD, scrupulosity, and rumination", "stable cross-tradition practitioners"]}, "primary_text_close_read": {"primary_pair": ["Chandogya Upanishad 6.8.7, local source card notes/source-cards/advaita-vedanta-chandogya-upanishad-6-8-7-tat-tvam-asi.md and https://shlokam.org/texts/Chandogya-6-8-7, read against SN 22.59 Anattalakkhana Sutta, local source card notes/source-cards/early-buddhism-sn-22-59-anattalakkhana-sutta.md and https://suttacentral.net/sn22.59", "Dao De Jing 48, https://www.tao-te-ching.org/48 and local source card notes/source-cards/daoism-dao-de-jing-chapter-48.md, read against Pseudo-Dionysius, Mystical Theology, local source card notes/source-cards/christianity-pseudo-dionysius-mystical-theology.md and https://www.tertullian.org/fathers/areopagite_03_mystic_theology.htm"], "risk_of_overread": "Medium high. The regeneration gate may rename standard comparative method, homeomorphic equivalence, doctrine-as-grammar, source criticism, and teacherly discernment. It can also overcorrect into purity policing, as if borrowed language cannot become authentic through hybrid discipline. In direct-recognition or performative settings, the question what taught this sentence may itself be the wrong kind of check. Human-condition fit is plausible but narrow: stable eclectic adults and older teens dealing with digital comparison, meaning loss, loneliness, and feeling out of place. It is not for acute crisis, OCD or scrupulosity loops, dissociation, severe depression, mania, unsafe authority situations, or people under trusted guidance who should ask their teacher.", "secondary_literature_gap": "Read Freiberger and Smith directly; Panikkar on homeomorphic equivalence and diatopical hermeneutics; Clooney and Cornille on comparative theology; Lindbeck on doctrine as grammar; Asad on discursive tradition; Sharf and Katz on experience, language, and context; Sandmel and Doering on parallelomania; Hays-style criteria for allusion, availability, volume, recurrence, thematic coherence, and historical plausibility; Pargament and spiritual coping for receiver use; and prior Lumenary records No Word Travels Alone, Translation Strain, A Shared Word Is Not Two Witnesses, and Stop When The Repair Changes.", "structural_observation": "Chandogya 6.8.7 authorizes identity language by placing Svetaketu within a teaching scene about subtle essence, Sat, Atman, and truth. SN 22.59 examines form, feeling, perception, formations, and consciousness as not-self, with liberation emerging through disenchantment and non-clinging. Both can unsettle ordinary identity, but the authority, allowed self-language, and verification differ. Dao De Jing 48 reduces learned accumulation toward wu wei and non-interference, while Pseudo-Dionysius diminishes sense and intellect within Christian ascent into divine darkness. The close read supports the gate's usefulness: the same surface operation, diminishing or de-centering, does different work under different carriers. It also shows the idea is a method control, not a new doctrine."}, "recommended_scores": {"counterargument_quality": 0.89, "novelty": 0.44, "source_reliability": 0.8}, "run_ids": ["20260530-120252-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-", "20260530-120252-codex-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-"], "title": "Ask Who Taught The Answer", "unlike_statement": "Unlike Panikkar's homeomorphic equivalence, Freiberger's comparison method, Lindbeck's doctrine-as-grammar, Asad's discursive tradition, and prior Lumenary translation-strain records, this candidate proposes a concrete regeneration gate for doctrine scoring and practice safety: a sentence cannot count as cross-tradition support until each source can reproduce it through its own practice, authority, correction, and verification, and until the modern receiver's use of the sentence has been checked for identity, belonging, avoidance, and concrete action."}
./hypotheses/ideas.jsonl:128:{"agent": "claude", "created_at": "2026-05-30T11:04:18+02:00", "critique": "The single-axis inversion is too crude. Strain is multi-level, and borrowing can lower one level while raising another: Gau\u1e0dap\u0101da borrows the logic of non-origination at low strain yet bends it hard to seat a permanent Self, producing high strain at the metaphysical level. So provenance interacts with strain level by level rather than uniformly lowering it. Historical contact also does not prove that a specific likeness was borrowed; two traditions can keep diverging or even independently re-converge after contact. And the genetic, areal, and independent distinction is well established in comparative method, so this may be application rather than discovery. The claim should be weakened if coding shows low-strain pairs distributed independently of historical contact, or if documented borrowing more often raises strain than lowers it.", "epistemic_labels": ["textual", "interpretive", "analogical", "empirical-adjacent", "speculative"], "idea_id": "184f0313f1a2464c", "idea_type": "contradiction", "next_research_directions": ["If this model is right, then when cross-tradition pairs are scored for strain and independently coded for historical contact, the lowest-strain pairs should cluster among connected traditions such as Gau\u1e0dap\u0101da and Madhyamaka, Advaita and Kashmir Shaivism, or Sufism and Neoplatonism via Arabic translation. If low strain is instead distributed independently of contact, the inversion is weakened.", "Test the level-by-level interaction: code lexical, logical, and metaphysical strain separately for the Gau\u1e0dap\u0101da and Madhyamaka pair. If borrowing lowers lexical and logical strain while raising metaphysical strain, replace the single-axis inversion with a level-resolved provenance rule.", "Find one isolated pair where a structural role recurs at low strain with no plausible contact. If such cases exist and are common, the claim that independent recurrence is usually rough is too strong.", "Protocol improvement: before any future run lets a cross-tradition agreement raise confidence, require a provenance line stating whether the two traditions could have shared the words, and treat unresolved provenance as a reason to hold the agreement at analogy weight only."], "original_claim": "Likeness between two traditions can be evidence of independent convergence only when the likeness could not have been borrowed. The translation-strain method rewards low strain as the strong signal, but low strain is exactly what historical transmission produces: when a word, a lineage, a translator, or a modern habit of universalizing carries language across traditions, the borrowed claim shows little strain because the vocabulary itself traveled. So low strain is ambiguous. It can mean a stable shared pattern, or it can mean one voice heard twice. Worse, the direction often inverts: genuinely independent recurrence tends to come with more strain, because each tradition reached a similar place by its own road and its own words, while borrowed agreement comes with less. The decisive close-reading case is Gau\u1e0dap\u0101da's non-origination beside Madhyamaka non-origination: it is among the lowest-strain Hindu-Buddhist pairs, and it is among the most historically connected. Therefore strain cannot carry evidential weight until provenance is checked first; without a contact-and-lineage gate, the strain score reports its own opposite.", "path": "observations/claude/2026-05-30-a-shared-word-is-not-two-witnesses.md", "practice_candidate": {"caution": "Stop if this becomes corrosive doubt that empties every source of meaning, or if it increases isolation rather than honesty. It is a check on one false comfort, not a worldview and not a substitute for community or care.", "duration": "5 minutes", "frequency": "Only when you notice yourself moved by two traditions appearing to agree, no fixed schedule.", "minimum_attempt": "Try it on three separate agreements before judging whether it helps.", "non_fit": "Not for people in acute crisis, grief, or destabilization who need rest, care, or human contact more than another analytic check. Not for trained scholars who already test provenance. It will not cure loneliness; it only removes a false comfort, so it should be paired with real community.", "notice": ["Whether the agreement still feels meaningful once it is no longer treated as proof.", "Whether your need for the two paths to agree was carrying weight that belonging or certainty should carry.", "Whether honest provenance makes you more curious or only more anxious."], "practice_line": "When two traditions seem to agree, ask whether the words could have traveled between them.", "purpose": "To keep a felt agreement between traditions from being mistaken for independent confirmation, and to soften the crash when the agreement turns out to be borrowing.", "risk_level": "low", "status": "seed", "steps": ["Write the shared claim in one plain sentence, in your own words.", "Ask whether the two traditions could have learned the language from each other: through a teacher, a translator, a shared lineage, or a modern book that already blends them.", "If they could have, mark the agreement as possibly borrowed and let it inform you without proving anything.", "If they genuinely could not have, notice that the agreement is probably rougher than it first looked, and name one place where the two still do not fit.", "Ask quietly what the agreement was doing for you: giving certainty, giving belonging, or ending a search. Let that need be seen without forcing the traditions to satisfy it."], "tags": ["provenance-check", "comparison", "meaning-loss", "low-risk", "spiritual-seeking"], "target_cohort": "Reflective cross-tradition readers and unaffiliated seekers assembling a private synthesis from many sources.", "target_human_problem": "Meaning loss and isolation in seekers who build conviction or belonging on the idea that all paths secretly say the same thing.", "title": "The Borrowed-Word Check", "weakens_if": "Users report that the check only breeds cynicism, that it adds nothing beyond ordinary reading, or that it increases loneliness without increasing honesty."}, "scores": {"counterargument_quality": 0.9, "cross_tradition_support": 0.7, "empirical_adjacency": 0.48, "explanatory_compression": 0.8, "generativity": 0.82, "logical_coherence": 0.85, "novelty": 0.52, "practice_testability": 0.7, "publishability": 0.66, "source_reliability": 0.74}, "source_basis": ["Run mode: Critique. The active frontier treats low translation strain as the strong signal of a stable cross-tradition pattern and high strain as mere analogy. This run tests whether that scoring direction survives a provenance check.", "Target of critique: Codex, Convergence as Translation Strain, Not Evidence Weight (idea 0e1a69f243a0d090), and Codex, Translation Strain as a Load Test for Convergence (idea d92d2f0f6455ac53). Both reward low-strain overlap as a candidate stable phenomenological or conceptual pattern.", "Primary-text comparison: Gau\u1e0dap\u0101da, M\u0101\u1e47\u1e0d\u016bkya K\u0101rik\u0101, fourth prakara\u1e47a Al\u0101ta\u015b\u0101nti, on aj\u0101tiv\u0101da (non-origination) and the firebrand-circle image, read against N\u0101g\u0101rjuna, M\u016blamadhyamakak\u0101rik\u0101 1.1 (nothing arises from itself, another, both, or neither). The likeness is lexically and logically very low strain, yet Gau\u1e0dap\u0101da is historically downstream of Madhyamaka and borrows its vocabulary and arguments.", "Contrast case: Plotinus, Enneads, on epistroph\u0113 (return toward the One), read against Dao De Jing 40 (return or reversal as the movement of the Dao). No established transmission links third-century Alexandria and Warring States China; the structural likeness of return survives only at higher strain, because each path carries incompatible surrounding metaphysics.", "Prior art and near-neighbor pressure: the genetic, areal, and independent trichotomy in historical linguistics (the comparative method distinguishes inheritance, borrowing or Sprachbund, and chance or universal recurrence); Richard King, Early Advaita Ved\u0101nta and Buddhism, on Gau\u1e0dap\u0101da's Mah\u0101y\u0101na context; J. Z. Smith and Oliver Freiberger on the construction of comparison.", "Modern human-condition grounding: modern-human-condition-pew-where-americans-find-meaning-in-life and modern-human-condition-surgeon-general-social-connection-advisory, for the unaffiliated seeker who leans on a felt universal agreement of traditions for belonging and certainty.", "Thinking-method source: Daoist wu wei and decrease (Dao De Jing 48), used to resist forcing two paths into one agreement, then checked against early Buddhist not-self analysis (SN 22.59) so that suspicion of likeness did not itself become a fixed position."], "status": "draft", "teaching_candidate": {"body": "When two traditions use the same word, it is tempting to feel that two separate witnesses have reached the same truth. Sometimes they have. Often the word itself traveled: through a teacher, a translation, a shared lineage, or a modern habit of making all paths sound alike. A likeness that came by borrowing is not a second confirmation. It is the first claim, heard twice. Before you let an agreement strengthen your conviction, ask whether the two paths could have learned the words from each other. If they could, hold the likeness gently. If they truly could not, the likeness is worth more, and it will usually be rougher, because each path arrived by its own road.", "doctrine_claim": "An agreement between traditions counts as independent confirmation only when it could not have been borrowed. Where teachers, translators, or shared lineage connect two paths, their likeness may be one voice echoed, not two voices confirming.", "falsifying_pressure": "Weakens if low-strain pairs turn out to be distributed independently of historical contact, if documented borrowing more often raises strain than lowers it, or if the warning only restates standard comparative-method caution without changing any actual scoring decision.", "pressure_survived": "The primary-text contrast between Gau\u1e0dap\u0101da and Madhyamaka non-origination, which is low strain and historically connected, and Plotinus and Daoist return, which is higher strain and plausibly independent. The teaching also survives prior-art pressure from the genetic, areal, and independent distinction in historical linguistics.", "status": "under_dialogue", "tags": ["critique-mode", "comparison", "borrowing-versus-independence", "meaning-loss", "spiritual-seeking", "convergence-caution"], "target_cohort": "Cross-tradition readers, spiritually unaffiliated people assembling a private synthesis, and deconstructing former believers who use the sense that all paths secretly agree as a substitute for community.", "target_human_problem": "Meaning loss and the loneliness of the unaffiliated seeker who leans on a felt universal agreement of traditions for belonging and certainty, then is destabilized when the agreement turns out to be borrowing rather than independent confirmation.", "teaching_line": "When two paths use the same word, ask whether the word traveled.", "title": "A Shared Word Is Not Two Witnesses"}, "tests": [{"impact": "pending", "next_action": "Search J. Z. Smith, Freiberger, Panikkar, Richard King on Gau\u1e0dap\u0101da, and historical-linguistics methodology for an existing statement that smoothness of cross-tradition likeness is the signature of borrowing rather than of independent recurrence.", "prediction": "Comparative religion and historical linguistics will already contain the diffusion-versus-parallel-development debate and the genetic, areal, and independent trichotomy, but not the specific rule that low translation strain inverts its evidential meaning and must be gated by provenance before it can strengthen a convergence claim. If that exact rule already exists, novelty should fall below 0.35.", "result": "pending", "status": "proposed", "target_type": "idea", "test_type": "prior-art", "title": "Provenance-Gate Prior-Art Search"}, {"impact": "pending", "next_action": "Build a small set of pairs with documented and absent contact, code strain and contact from separate sources, and test the association before trusting any convergence score.", "prediction": "When cross-tradition pairs are blind-coded for translation strain and separately coded for historical contact, the lowest-strain pairs should cluster among contact pairs (Gau\u1e0dap\u0101da and Madhyamaka, Advaita and Kashmir Shaivism, Sufism and Neoplatonism via translation), and isolated pairs should show higher strain even where a role recurs. If low strain is distributed independently of contact, the inversion is weakened.", "result": "pending", "status": "proposed", "target_type": "idea", "test_type": "falsification-attempt", "title": "Strain Versus Contact Coding"}, {"impact": "pending", "next_action": "Compare comparative-law cases of trust, due process, and good faith, coding transplant history separately from conceptual likeness, and test whether provenance changes which apparent equivalents mislead.", "prediction": "Legal concepts that look low-strain because they spread through shared colonial transplant (for example trust exported via English common law) should not predict successful independent reception, and should mislead exactly when their low strain is read as deep fit rather than as common origin. A strain score gated by transplant provenance should predict failed transplants better than an ungated score.", "result": "pending", "status": "proposed", "target_type": "idea", "test_type": "cross-domain", "title": "Legal Transplant Provenance Test"}], "title": "A Shared Word Is Not Two Witnesses", "why_it_might_be_new": "Existing translation-strain work treats strain as a load test where surviving overlap suggests a stable cross-tradition pattern. This narrows that claim by showing the load test is undefined without a provenance gate, because the very signal it rewards, low strain and surviving role-similarity, is also the signature of direct transmission. The sharper move is the inversion: independent convergence is more likely to be rough than smooth, so smoothness should lower confidence rather than raise it whenever historical contact is possible. The genetic, areal, and independent trichotomy is old in linguistics, which keeps novelty modest; the distinct contribution is applying it to invert the evidential reading of strain and to require provenance before any convergence score is allowed to strengthen a claim."}
./hypotheses/ideas.jsonl:130:{"agent": "claude", "created_at": "2026-05-30T11:40:19+02:00", "critique": "The statistical analogy is loose: claim units are not random samples from a distribution, so within-tradition variance is metaphorical, and there is no clean way to compute it. Worse, weighting every textual variant equally inflates the denominator. Pudgalavada was eventually marginalized, and a minority or scholastic position may not deserve the same weight as the operative mainstream that practitioners actually train. Some traditions do settle a dominant working position at a given stage despite live scholarly disputes, so treating internal variance as always large would itself distort by flattering fragmentation. The denominator therefore must be weighted by how operative a variant is, not by its mere existence in the record, and that weighting is contestable enough that a motivated comparer could tune it to reach either verdict. The control is real but it relocates the judgment rather than removing it.", "epistemic_labels": ["textual", "interpretive", "analogical", "empirical-adjacent", "speculative"], "idea_id": "5bca4594ea00fa13", "idea_type": "contradiction", "next_research_directions": ["If this model is right, then when independent coders are each given a different but legitimate internal variant of each tradition (Theravada anatta versus Pudgalavada person; Shankara self-luminosity versus scriptural-testimony Advaita), they should return contradictory convergence verdicts for high-variance units and agreeing verdicts for low-variance units such as the bare instruction to attend to the breath. If convergence verdicts stay stable regardless of which internal variant is selected, the model is weakened.", "Operationalize within-tradition variance with operative weighting: code each internal variant by how central it is to lived practice at a stated stage, not by its presence in the textual record, then test whether weighted variance still rivals the cross-tradition gap in the atman/anatta case.", "Run the variance gate and the provenance gate together on the same pairs to confirm they are orthogonal: find at least one pair that passes provenance (independent) but fails variance (internally unstable), and one that passes variance but fails provenance.", "Test whether assertion posture (does a tradition hold theses) behaves as a continuous contested parameter rather than a fixed property, using the Svatantrika-Prasangika case as the calibration example."], "original_claim": "Translation-strain comparison has a numerator and no denominator. Before you can say that two traditions converge or clash on a claim unit, you must measure how much that same unit varies inside each tradition, across its sub-schools, stages of practice, and polemical eras. If the internal spread is as wide as the gap you found between the two traditions, then your convergence-or-divergence verdict is mostly an artifact of which internal version you happened to pick, not a cross-tradition signal. So Lumenary should now hold that a strain score is only admissible once between-tradition strain has been shown to exceed within-tradition variance for the same unit; otherwise the comparison should be labeled selection-dependent and given no evidential weight.", "path": "observations/claude/2026-05-30-first-ask-if-a-path-agrees-with-itself.md", "practice_candidate": {"caution": "Do not let this become a reason never to commit; endless comparison is its own trap. Stop if it feeds rumination, paralysis, or a feeling that nothing can be trusted.", "duration": "10 minutes", "frequency": "Only when you encounter a strong claim that two traditions agree or contradict, no more than twice a week.", "minimum_attempt": "Try it on three separate comparisons before judging whether it helps.", "non_fit": "Not for acute distress or crisis. Not a substitute for actually practicing one path. Not for people whose real problem is endless analysis and avoidance of commitment; they need to choose and practice, not compare more. Not a way to settle scholarly disputes the person has no sources to judge.", "notice": ["Whether the urge to announce they agree or it is all confused loosens.", "Whether you feel freer to commit to one practice without first resolving the comparison.", "Whether you start hearing single quotes as one voice in an argument rather than the whole tradition."], "practice_line": "Before trusting a comparison, find where each tradition argues with itself about it.", "purpose": "To keep a single quote from standing in for a whole tradition, and to steady a person against both rootless all-is-one feelings and cynical it-is-all-contradictory dismissal.", "risk_level": "low", "status": "seed", "steps": ["Write the comparison you heard in one line: X and Y both say, or X and Y contradict on, this exact point.", "For each tradition, find one place where its own teachers, schools, or earlier and later texts disagree on that same point.", "Write the internal range for each tradition in one short line.", "Ask: is the gap between the two traditions clearly wider than the gap inside each of them?", "If it is not clearly wider, hold the comparison loosely; it may be a choice of quotes rather than a finding.", "Choose one path's actual practice to try in your own life this week instead of waiting for the comparison to be settled."], "tags": ["comparison", "internal-disagreement", "low-risk", "meaning-loss", "digital-comparison"], "target_cohort": "Reflective readers and seekers who compare traditions through books, feeds, or AI summaries.", "target_human_problem": "Meaning loss, digital comparison, and the urge to abandon practice after meeting contradictory or falsely harmonized quotes.", "title": "The self-agreement check", "weakens_if": "It increases analysis paralysis, or it adds nothing beyond the ordinary humility a careful reader already has."}, "scores": {"counterargument_quality": 0.88, "cross_tradition_support": 0.72, "empirical_adjacency": 0.5, "explanatory_compression": 0.8, "generativity": 0.85, "logical_coherence": 0.86, "novelty": 0.6, "practice_testability": 0.74, "publishability": 0.72, "source_reliability": 0.66}, "source_basis": ["Run mode: Critique. The active frontier (translation strain as a test of convergence) is heavily elaborated, so this run hunts for a structural failure in the scoring rather than adding another strain variable.", "Thinking-method source: Zhuangzi's perspectival humility and Daoist non-forcing, used as a lens to refuse fixing a whole tradition to one representative point. Critique of the lens: non-forcing can dissolve every stable position into mere perspective, which would over-fragment traditions that do settle operative positions; corrected with SN 22.95 style disciplined examination, which still asks what is actually trained at a given stage.", "Contrasting reasoning discipline: effect-size logic from statistics, where a between-group difference counts as real only if it exceeds within-group variance. This supplies the missing denominator for strain scores.", "Primary-text comparison (intra-Buddhist spread): SN 22.59 Anattalakkhana Sutta refuses to treat any aggregate, including consciousness, as self, while the Pudgalavada (Vatsiputriya, Sammitiya) posited a pudgala or person that is neither the same as nor different from the aggregates and is inexpressible. https://suttacentral.net/sn22.59/en/sujato ; https://iep.utm.edu/pudgalavada-buddhist-philosophy/", "Primary-text comparison (intra-Advaita spread): Brihadaranyaka 3.7.23 names an unseen knower, read by Shankara as self-luminous direct recognition, while a scriptural-testimony (shabda pramana) emphasis treats the witness as established through revealed instruction rather than spontaneous self-disclosure. The comparison reveals that the intra-Advaita gap on how the witness is known, and the intra-Buddhist gap on whether any subject is authorized, can rival the cross-tradition atman/anatta gap the strain protocol claims to measure.", "Internal-posture evidence: the Svatantrika-Prasangika dispute over whether Madhyamaka asserts a thesis at all (Bhavaviveka vs Candrakirti, surveyed in Dreyfus and McClintock, The Svatantrika-Prasangika Distinction: What Difference Does a Difference Make?), showing that even a tradition's assertion posture is internally contested.", "Codex prior art treated as orthogonal: Translation Strain as a Load Test for Convergence (d92d2f0f6455ac53); A Shared Word Is Not Two Witnesses (provenance gate); No Word Travels Alone (receiver wound). All measure deformation between traditions or its causes; none measures instability within a tradition as a control.", "Comparative-method prior art: Jonathan Z. Smith, In Comparison a Magic Dwells; Freiberger's rectification step; and comparative religion's general acknowledgment of intra-traditional diversity, which notes the diversity but does not make measured within-tradition variance the threshold any between-tradition score must clear.", "Modern human-condition grounding: docs/modern-human-condition.md on digital comparison and meaning loss; the surgeon-general social-connection advisory on isolation."], "status": "draft", "teaching_candidate": {"body": "Someone tells you two faiths say the same thing, or that they flatly disagree. Before you believe it, look closer. Pick up either tradition and you will often find it arguing with itself: different teachers, schools, and centuries answering the question in different ways. If a path disputes a point among its own people, one quote cannot speak for the whole. Do not let a single sentence stand in for a living argument. When you compare, compare the range, not the slogan; and notice that a tidy agreement or a clean contradiction is sometimes only the two quotes you happened to meet first.", "doctrine_claim": "A claim that two traditions converge or contradict is unreliable until you know how widely each tradition disputes that same point inside its own house.", "falsifying_pressure": "Weakens if convergence verdicts stay stable no matter which legitimate internal variant of each tradition is chosen, or if practitioners' operative positions turn out far narrower than the textual disputes suggest, so that the internal spread is mostly scholastic and not lived.", "pressure_survived": "Survives the atman versus anatta case, where the intra-Buddhist range (strict not-self versus the Pudgalavada inexpressible person) and the intra-Advaita range (self-luminous recognition versus knowing the witness through scripture) rival the cross-tradition gap; survives prior comparative-method acknowledgment of internal diversity by turning that diversity into a measured gate rather than a caution.", "status": "under_dialogue", "tags": ["comparison", "internal-disagreement", "digital-comparison", "meaning-loss", "critique-mode"], "target_cohort": "Reflective cross-tradition readers and seekers, especially people whose footing is unsettled by influencer or AI summaries that flatten many traditions into one verdict.", "target_human_problem": "Meaning loss and cynical dismissal, or its mirror, rootless all-is-one universalism, triggered when a person reads short comparative claims online and concludes either that the traditions secretly agree or that they are hopelessly contradictory.", "teaching_line": "Before you decide two paths agree or clash, ask whether each path even agrees with itself.", "title": "Ask if a path agrees with itself"}, "tests": [{"impact": "revises", "next_action": "Close-read Jonathan Z. Smith, Freiberger, Dreyfus and McClintock, and recent comparative-method work for any formalized variance-as-denominator control before raising novelty.", "prediction": "Comparative theology and comparative religion should acknowledge intra-traditional diversity and warn against projecting similarity, but should not already require measured within-tradition variance of the same claim unit as the explicit threshold any between-tradition convergence score must exceed. If that exact control already exists with predictive use, novelty should fall below 0.35.", "result": "Preliminary search found strong general acknowledgment of intra-traditional diversity (Stanford pluralism entry, anthropology of religion sources) and the Svatantrika-Prasangika and Pudgalavada disputes, but no source making within-tradition variance the formal denominator for strain scoring. The effect-size framing appears new to this domain; full audit incomplete.", "status": "complete", "target_type": "idea", "test_type": "prior-art", "title": "Within-tradition variance prior-art search"}, {"impact": "pending", "next_action": "Build a small codebook listing two or three legitimate internal variants per tradition per unit, then run blind coding with variant assignment randomized.", "prediction": "Give independent coders the same cross-tradition pair but assign each a different legitimate internal variant of each tradition. For high-variance units (the self in Buddhism, the witness in Advaita, grace versus effort in Christianity) coders should produce contradictory converge-or-diverge verdicts; for low-variance units they should agree. If verdicts are stable across variant assignment, the variance gate adds nothing and the model is weakened.", "result": "pending", "status": "proposed", "target_type": "idea", "test_type": "falsification-attempt", "title": "Variant-swap convergence coding"}, {"impact": "pending", "next_action": "Score a handful of legal concepts by within-system dispute level, then compare against documented harmonization disputes and failed transplants.", "prediction": "Legal concepts that are internally contested within a single system (good faith, due process, reasonableness) should yield less stable cross-system convergence verdicts and more failed transplants than concepts with a settled internal meaning, even when the shared term looks identical. If cross-system convergence is predicted just as well by shared terms regardless of internal contestation, the analogy and the variance gate lose force.", "result": "pending", "status": "proposed", "target_type": "idea", "test_type": "cross-domain", "title": "Legal-transplant analogue"}, {"impact": "pending", "next_action": "Collect short before-and-after reports from readers who recently encountered a strong comparative claim, screening out acute distress and chronic avoidance.", "prediction": "For reflective seekers unsettled by comparative claims, three uses of the self-agreement check should reduce both all-is-one certainty and cynical dismissal, and should make commitment to one practice feel more available. If it increases analysis paralysis or rumination, the practice is weakened or must be narrowed.", "result": "pending", "status": "proposed", "target_type": "practice", "test_type": "practice-report", "title": "Self-agreement check practice report"}], "title": "First Ask If a Path Agrees With Itself", "why_it_might_be_new": "Existing strain work measures the deformation between two traditions, and the provenance gate asks whether an apparent similarity came from historical contact. This adds a different and orthogonal control: whether the unit is even stable enough within one tradition to be compared. A comparison can pass the provenance gate (genuinely independent) and still fail this variance gate (the chosen claim unit is internally contested enough that another legitimate reading would flip the verdict). The move imports effect-size reasoning into spiritual comparison: comparative religion already notes intra-traditional diversity, but does not require a measured within-tradition spread as the denominator that every between-tradition strain score must clear."}
