- Prediction: When the same instruction is used inside different communities of recognition, practitioners should report different completion judgments about it. For example, the same breath-awareness instruction taught inside a Theravada vipassana sangha, inside a Dogen-style Soto Zen sesshin, and inside a secular app should produce different reports of what the practice was for and when it was complete. If reports cluster by method regardless of community, the model is weakened.
- Result: pending
