{"title":"A Test Is Not A Home","idea_type":"synthesis","source_basis":["Mode: Critique. The active frontier, translation strain as a test of convergence, is narrowed: the full strain sheet is a doctrine and publication gate, not a direct remedy for loneliness.","One-page strain sheet now required for doctrine use: claim unit, role, ontology, agency, practice aim, authority, verification, provenance, source-language wording, English smoothing, internal dispute range, what is bent, what is dropped, what is added, and whether role-similarity survives.","Primary-text comparison: Chandogya Upanishad 6.8.7, https://shlokam.org/texts/Chandogya-6-8-7, read against SN 22.59, https://suttacentral.net/sn22.59/en/bodhi. Both unsettle ordinary identity, but Chandogya authorizes identity with subtle essence while SN 22.59 refuses ownership of all aggregates, including consciousness.","Primary-text comparison: Gaudapada's Mandukya Karika source card read against Nagarjuna's MMK source card. The shared non-origination dialectic has low strain partly because of historical Buddhist influence, while the metaphysical result differs sharply. Low strain can signal borrowing, not independent support.","Practitioner-method source: Dao De Jing 48, decrease and non-forcing. I used it to subtract forced sameness before scoring a comparison. Critique of the method: reduction can treat borrowed hope as contamination, so it was corrected by social-connection pressure and a contact-first practice.","Near prior art: Jonathan Z. Smith, In Comparison a Magic Dwells, https://classics.osu.edu/sites/classics.osu.edu/files/Magic_Dwells.pdf; Oliver Freiberger, Elements of a Comparative Methodology in the Study of Religion, https://www.mdpi.com/2077-1444/9/2/38; Raimon Panikkar, homeomorphic equivalence, https://www.raimon-panikkar.org/english/gloss-homeomorphic.html.","Modern human-condition grounding: U.S. Surgeon General social connection advisory source card, https://www.hhs.gov/sites/default/files/surgeon-general-social-connection-advisory.pdf; Pew Where Americans Find Meaning in Life source card, https://www.pewresearch.org/religion/2018/11/20/where-americans-find-meaning-in-life/; U.S. Surgeon General social media advisory source card, https://www.hhs.gov/surgeongeneral/reports-and-publications/youth-mental-health/social-media/index.html.","Local near-neighbor pressure: No Word Travels Alone, A Shared Word Is Not Two Witnesses, Ask Who Taught The Answer, Sameness Can Be the Fingerprint of Borrowing, and Contact Before Claim. This record should merge with them unless the doctrine-versus-belonging split proves useful in tests."],"original_claim":"A test that protects doctrine can harm a lonely person if it is handed to them as medicine. When two traditions seem to agree, the full strain sheet should ask what each path must bend, drop, or add before the agreement counts. But when a person uses a borrowed sentence for hope, belonging, or direction, the first test should be contact and conduct: does the sentence move them toward a real person, duty, repair, help, or community before it becomes an identity claim. What now holds is a split rule: doctrine should be provenance-first; wounded use should be contact-first. A sentence is not suspect because it traveled. It becomes suspect when it replaces correction, action, grief work, help-seeking, or belonging with private certainty or public display.","why_it_might_be_new":"Smith, Freiberger, and Panikkar already make comparison disciplined, invented, and role-sensitive. Lindbeck and Asad are also close because they tie doctrine to communal grammar and traditioned practice. The exact difference is the split use rule: the same comparison sheet should be strict for doctrine-building and restrained for lonely seekers. Prior local records already named provenance, receiver wound, and borrowing; this record lowers novelty and adds one sharper claim, that a valid research gate should not become a solo belonging practice unless it demonstrably increases contact and conduct.","critique":"The split may excuse shallow appropriation by letting seekers delay provenance too long. It may also overstate loneliness as the main human wound when some users need accuracy, recovery support, or ordinary rest more than contact. The strongest anomaly is an authorized hybrid lineage or comparative theology setting where borrowed language is already corrected by living teachers and community, so provenance and contact are not separate stages. Another anomaly is direct-recognition practice: some traditions will object that the truth of recognition is not validated by contact first. If teachers and practitioners show that ordinary guidance handles these cases better than this split, or if contact-first practice increases shame, unsafe disclosure, or confusion, the model should narrow or retire.","epistemic_labels":["textual","interpretive","phenomenological","empirical-adjacent","analogical","speculative"],"scores":{"novelty":0.44,"generativity":0.88,"cross_tradition_support":0.72,"logical_coherence":0.84,"explanatory_compression":0.82,"empirical_adjacency":0.63,"practice_testability":0.88,"counterargument_quality":0.91,"source_reliability":0.8,"publishability":0.69},"next_research_directions":["Build the doctrine-facing one-page strain sheet with the required fields, then test whether blind coders can use it reliably on Chandogya versus SN 22.59, Gaudapada versus Nagarjuna, Daoist non-action versus contemplative surrender, and fana versus self-release.","If this model is right, then a full provenance sheet should improve doctrine scoring, while a contact-first version should outperform the full sheet for lonely seekers by increasing real contact and reducing rumination. If the full sheet helps both cohorts equally, or contact-first does not change contact, the split is weakened.","If source-language and English-smoothing fields matter, then apparent agreements produced by modern English perennialist vocabulary should lose support once source-language carriers are restored. If scores remain unchanged, the added field is unnecessary.","Search comparative theology, pastoral discernment, seeker spirituality, spiritual-bypassing literature, OCD checking models, and social-connection interventions for exact prior versions of the split use rule before raising novelty.","Protocol improvement: before turning any research gate into a practice, ask whether the gate reduces the named wound or merely gives the wounded person a more refined way to stay alone."],"teaching_candidate":{"title":"Let The Test Stay A Test","teaching_line":"Use a test to guard truth, not to replace contact.","doctrine_claim":"Cross-tradition agreement should pass a strict carrier test before it supports doctrine, but a lonely seeker should first test a borrowed sentence by contact, conduct, and correction.","body":"A careful test can protect truth. It can also become a room you never leave.\n\nWhen you compare traditions, be strict. Ask what each path teaches, who may correct it, how it is practiced, and what must be changed for the match to work.\n\nWhen a sentence is helping you endure, begin closer to life. Ask what real act it asks today. Bring it to a person, a duty, a repair, a request for help, or a community that can answer back. Do not let a borrowed sentence become your identity before it has made you more honest and more available.","target_human_problem":"Loneliness, meaning loss, digital comparison, and feeling out of place intensified by borrowed spiritual language that becomes identity display or private certainty.","target_cohort":"Stable spiritually eclectic adults and older teens who gather spiritual language online or across traditions and are tempted to turn a moving sentence into identity, proof, or public authority.","pressure_survived":"Survived prior-art pressure from comparative method, homeomorphic equivalence, doctrine-as-grammar, provenance checks, receiver-wound records, and modern social-connection pressure by narrowing itself to a split use rule.","falsifying_pressure":"Weakens if the split adds nothing beyond ordinary teacher guidance, if contact-first practice does not reduce loneliness or identity display, or if it delays needed provenance in ways that increase confident misuse.","status":"under_dialogue","tags":["translation-strain","critique-mode","borrowed-language","loneliness","meaning-loss","digital-comparison","doctrine-gate"]},"practice_candidate":{"title":"Contact First, Trace Later","practice_line":"Before making a borrowed sentence your identity, bring it to one real act or person.","purpose":"To test whether a borrowed spiritual sentence is moving into conduct and connection, or becoming private certainty, avoidance, or public identity display.","target_human_problem":"Loneliness, meaning loss, digital comparison, and feeling out of place soothed by abstract agreement instead of real belonging or repair.","target_cohort":"Stable adults and older teens with basic support who read across traditions, collect spiritual claims online, or feel pulled to post or organize life around a powerful borrowed sentence.","non_fit":"Not for acute crisis, psychosis, mania, severe depression, active addiction withdrawal, dissociation, unsafe relationships, OCD or scrupulosity loops, coercive communities, or people under trusted guidance who should ask their teacher or clinician.","duration":"15 minutes plus a 24 hour delay before posting or making a major identity claim.","frequency":"Only when a borrowed sentence feels important enough to post, repeat as yours, or use for a decision. No more than twice per week.","minimum_attempt":"Try it on three separate sentences across two weeks, stopping earlier if shame, checking, panic, or isolation increases.","steps":["Write the exact sentence you want to claim, post, or build on.","Name its use: doctrine, public authority, private hope, decision guidance, or comfort.","If it is doctrine or public authority, pause and complete the full strain sheet: claim unit, role, ontology, agency, practice aim, authority, verification, provenance, what is bent, what is dropped, and what is added.","If it is hope or direction, name one concrete act it asks in the next 24 hours toward a person, duty, repair, help, or community.","Do that act before posting the sentence or making it part of your identity.","If the sentence would shape a major decision, bring it to one trustworthy person or community that can answer back.","After 24 hours, write whether the sentence made you more connected, honest, careful, and correctable, or more isolated, performative, certain, or avoidant."],"notice":["Whether the sentence produces contact or only a self-image.","Whether the sentence makes you more open to correction or more defended against it.","Whether delaying public display reduces urgency or increases anxious checking.","Whether the real act reveals that the sentence was asking for repair, rest, help, grief, or ordinary responsibility."],"caution":"Stop if the practice increases shame, obsessive checking, panic, dissociation, contempt, unsafe disclosure, withdrawal, or dependency on an unsafe person. Use qualified human support for clinical, legal, relational, or safety crises.","weakens_if":"Weakens if ordinary journaling, teacher guidance, or a simple wait-before-posting rule works as well, or if the practice lowers posting but leaves loneliness, conduct, and real contact unchanged.","risk_level":"low","status":"seed","tags":["contact-first","borrowed-language","loneliness","meaning-loss","digital-comparison","low-risk"]},"tests":[{"title":"Split Rule Prior-Art Audit","test_type":"prior-art","target_type":"idea","prediction":"Close prior work should cover disciplined comparison, doctrine as communal grammar, seeker bricolage, and warnings against compulsive checking, but should not already state the exact split that doctrine needs provenance-first testing while lonely seeker use needs contact-first fruit testing. If that exact split exists, novelty should fall below 0.3.","result":"Preliminary web and local search found strong near-neighbors in Smith, Freiberger, Panikkar, Lindbeck, Asad, comparative theology, spiritual-bypassing concerns, and multiple local records. The exact split use rule was not found in this pass, but novelty is lowered because the pieces are well known.","impact":"revises","next_action":"Read comparative theology, pastoral discernment, Robert Wuthnow on seeker spirituality, Sherry Turkle on conversation, and OCD checking literature before treating the split as more than an applied synthesis.","status":"complete"},{"title":"Full Sheet Versus Contact First Pilot","test_type":"practice-report","target_type":"practice","prediction":"For stable cross-tradition readers with loneliness or meaning loss, contact-first practice should increase actual relational contact, repair actions, and willingness to receive correction more than the full provenance sheet or ordinary journaling, while producing less rumination. If it only reduces posting or increases checking, the practice is weakened.","result":"pending","impact":"pending","next_action":"Run a small screened four-arm pilot: full sheet, contact-first, wait-before-posting, and ordinary journaling. Track loneliness, rumination, identity-display posts, concrete contact, repair actions, and distress at two and six weeks.","status":"proposed"},{"title":"Carrier Fields Reliability Test","test_type":"falsification-attempt","target_type":"idea","prediction":"Independent coders should reliably distinguish role, ontology, agency, practice aim, authority, verification, provenance, English smoothing, bent meaning, dropped meaning, and added meaning in narrow primary-text pairs. If coders cannot score these above chance, the doctrine sheet is too fine-grained to use.","result":"pending","impact":"pending","next_action":"Create a codebook and blind-code Chandogya versus SN 22.59, Mandukya Karika versus MMK, Dao De Jing 48 versus Pseudo-Dionysius, and one Sufi-Buddhist dissolution pair.","status":"proposed"},{"title":"Borrowing As Living Carrier Challenge","test_type":"falsification-attempt","target_type":"idea","prediction":"Authorized hybrid traditions should show cases where borrowed language becomes valid through new correction, practice, authority, and verification. If the strain sheet marks these as counterfeit, it is over-policing purity and must be revised.","result":"pending","impact":"pending","next_action":"Interview dual-trained practitioners and comparative theologians about cases where borrowed language became responsible rather than misleading.","status":"proposed"},{"title":"Legal Transplant Contact Test","test_type":"cross-domain","target_type":"idea","prediction":"In comparative law, low-strain terms such as trust, due process, equity, and good faith should mislead when they travel without matching institutions, authority, verification, and repair practices. If shared terms predict successful transfer without carrier fields, the analogy weakens.","result":"pending","impact":"pending","next_action":"Score legal-transplant cases by carrier fields and compare against known implementation disputes, especially where colonial or shared-language provenance produced false ease.","status":"proposed"}]}
